{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875300372,"sessionID":"ses_28595af03ffeB1qczelYixQTBJ","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6a9394001zV2dxddzlpfhRM","messageID":"msg_d7a6a793a001Dgbsfk6glSTl7n","sessionID":"ses_28595af03ffeB1qczelYixQTBJ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-004  \n6: **Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** M  \n9: \n10: Establish the HTTP service framework for the WorkloadManager component, providing RESTful APIs for managing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, health endpoints, and integration with the Kubernetes client-go library.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: HTTP Server Bootstrap\n17: \n18: The system SHALL provide a configurable HTTP server that can be started and gracefully shut down.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Server starts with configuration\n21: - **GIVEN** a valid server configuration with host, port, and handler registrations\n22: - **WHEN** the operator calls `server.Start()`\n23: - **THEN** the HTTP server SHALL bind to the configured address and begin accepting connections\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Server shuts down gracefully\n26: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server with active connections\n27: - **WHEN** the operator calls `server.Shutdown(ctx)` with a context timeout\n28: - **THEN** the server SHALL stop accepting new connections, wait for existing requests to complete (within timeout), and release resources\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Server configuration from environment\n31: - **GIVEN** environment variables `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_HOST` (default \"0.0.0.0\") and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_PORT` (default \"8080\")\n32: - **WHEN** the operator initializes the server configuration\n33: - **THEN** the configuration SHALL read from these environment variables with sensible defaults\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Server supports TLS configuration\n36: - **GIVEN** TLS certificate and key files specified in configuration\n37: - **WHEN** the operator starts the server with TLS enabled\n38: - **THEN** the server SHALL serve HTTPS using the provided certificates\n39: \n40: ---\n41: \n42: ### Requirement: Health and Readiness Endpoints\n43: \n44: The system SHALL expose standard Kubernetes health check endpoints for liveness and readiness probes.\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Liveness endpoint returns healthy\n47: - **GIVEN** the WorkloadManager HTTP server is running\n48: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/healthz`\n49: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 with body `{\"status\": \"ok\"}` when the process is alive\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Readiness endpoint reflects dependency health\n52: - **GIVEN** the WorkloadManager has initialized all dependencies (Kubernetes client, Redis connection)\n53: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/readyz`\n54: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 with body `{\"status\": \"ready\"}` when all dependencies are healthy\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Readiness endpoint returns not ready\n57: - **GIVEN** the WorkloadManager has a failed dependency (e.g., Kubernetes API unreachable)\n58: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/readyz`\n59: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 503 with body `{\"status\": \"not_ready\", \"reason\": \"<failure_reason>\"}`\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Health endpoint includes detailed checks\n62: - **GIVEN** the configuration enables verbose health checks\n63: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/healthz?verbose=true`\n64: - **THEN** the server SHALL return detailed health status for each registered health check component\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ### Requirement: RESTful API for AgentRuntime Resources\n69: \n70: The system SHALL expose RESTful HTTP endpoints for CRUD operations on AgentRuntime resources.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: List AgentRuntimes\n73: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime resources exist in namespace `default`\n74: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes`\n75: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 with a JSON list of AgentRuntime objects\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: Get single AgentRuntime\n78: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `test-runtime` exists in namespace `default`\n79: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime`\n80: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 with the AgentRuntime JSON object\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: Get non-existent AgentRuntime returns 404\n83: - **GIVEN** no AgentRuntime named `non-existent` exists in namespace `default`\n84: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/non-existent`\n85: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404 with error details\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Create AgentRuntime\n88: - **GIVEN** a valid AgentRuntime JSON payload\n89: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes` with the payload\n90: - **THEN** the server SHALL create the resource via Kubernetes API and return HTTP 201 with the created object\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Create invalid AgentRuntime returns 400\n93: - **GIVEN** an invalid AgentRuntime JSON payload (missing required fields)\n94: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes` with the invalid payload\n95: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 with validation error details\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Update AgentRuntime\n98: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named `test-runtime`\n99: - **WHEN** a PUT request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime` with updated spec\n100: - **THEN** the server SHALL update the resource and return HTTP 200 with the updated object\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: Delete AgentRuntime\n103: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named `test-runtime`\n104: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime`\n105: - **THEN** the server SHALL delete the resource and return HTTP 200 with the deleted object\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Watch AgentRuntimes\n108: - **GIVEN** the server supports streaming endpoints\n109: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes?watch=true`\n110: - **THEN** the server SHALL establish a streaming connection and emit ADDED/MODIFIED/DELETED events as resources change\n111: \n112: ---\n113: \n114: ### Requirement: RESTful API for CodeInterpreter Resources\n115: \n116: The system SHALL expose RESTful HTTP endpoints for CRUD operations on CodeInterpreter resources.\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: List CodeInterpreters\n119: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreter resources exist in namespace `default`\n120: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters`\n121: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 with a JSON list of CodeInterpreter objects\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Get single CodeInterpreter\n124: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `test-interpreter` exists in namespace `default`\n125: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters/test-interpreter`\n126: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 with the CodeInterpreter JSON object\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Create CodeInterpreter\n129: - **GIVEN** a valid CodeInterpreter JSON payload\n130: - **WHEN** a POST request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters` with the payload\n131: - **THEN** the server SHALL create the resource via Kubernetes API and return HTTP 201 with the created object\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Update CodeInterpreter\n134: - **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter named `test-interpreter`\n135: - **WHEN** a PUT request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters/test-interpreter` with updated spec\n136: - **THEN** the server SHALL update the resource and return HTTP 200 with the updated object\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Delete CodeInterpreter\n139: - **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter named `test-interpreter`\n140: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters/test-interpreter`\n141: - **THEN** the server SHALL delete the resource and return HTTP 200 with the deleted object\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: Watch CodeInterpreters\n144: - **GIVEN** the server supports streaming endpoints\n145: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters?watch=true`\n146: - **THEN** the server SHALL establish a streaming connection and emit ADDED/MODIFIED/DELETED events as resources change\n147: \n148: ---\n149: \n150: ### Requirement: Resource Status Endpoints\n151: \n152: The system SHALL expose endpoints for retrieving and updating resource status.\n153: \n154: #### Scenario: Get AgentRuntime status\n155: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `test-runtime` exists with status information\n156: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime/status`\n157: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 with only the status portion of the resource\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Update AgentRuntime status\n160: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named `test-runtime`\n161: - **WHEN** a PUT request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/test-runtime/status` with new status\n162: - **THEN** the server SHALL update only the status subresource and return HTTP 200\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: Get CodeInterpreter status\n165: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `test-interpreter` exists with status information\n166: - **WHEN** a GET request is made to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters/test-interpreter/status`\n167: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 200 with only the status portion of the resource\n168: \n169: ---\n170: \n171: ### Requirement: Kubernetes Client Integration\n172: \n173: The system SHALL integrate with the Kubernetes API using the generated client-go library.\n174: \n175: #### Scenario: Client initialization from in-cluster config\n176: - **GIVEN** the WorkloadManager is running inside a Kubernetes pod\n177: - **WHEN** the server initializes the Kubernetes client\n178: - **THEN** it SHALL use in-cluster configuration to connect to the Kubernetes API server\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: Client initialization from kubeconfig\n181: - **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig file at `~/.kube/config` when running outside the cluster\n182: - **WHEN** the server initializes the Kubernetes client\n183: - **THEN** it SHALL use the kubeconfig to connect to the Kubernetes API server\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: Client uses typed clientset\n186: - **GIVEN** the Kubernetes client is initialized\n187: - **WHEN** the server handles AgentRuntime API requests\n188: - **THEN** it SHALL use the generated `clientset.Interface` from `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: Client handles authentication\n191: - **GIVEN** the service account has proper RBAC permissions\n192: - **WHEN** the server makes API requests\n193: - **THEN** the client SHALL authenticate using the service account token and certificate\n194: \n195: ---\n196: \n197: ### Requirement: Request Routing and Middleware\n198: \n199: The system SHALL implement HTTP request routing with middleware support for cross-cutting concerns.\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Route registration\n202: - **GIVEN** the server is being configured\n203: - **WHEN** handlers are registered with the router\n204: - **THEN** each route SHALL be mapped to the correct HTTP method and path pattern\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Request logging middleware\n207: - **GIVEN** a request is received by the server\n208: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n209: - **THEN** the server SHALL log the request method, path, status code, and duration\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Request ID middleware\n212: - **GIVEN** a request is received without an `X-Request-ID` header\n213: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n214: - **THEN** the server SHALL generate a unique request ID and include it in response headers\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: CORS middleware\n217: - **GIVEN** CORS is enabled in configuration\n218: - **WHEN** a cross-origin request is received\n219: - **THEN** the server SHALL respond with appropriate CORS headers\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: Panic recovery middleware\n222: - **GIVEN** a request handler panics during execution\n223: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n224: - **THEN** the server SHALL recover from the panic, log the error, and return HTTP 500 without crashing\n225: \n226: #### Scenario: Authentication middleware\n227: - **GIVEN** authentication is enabled in configuration\n228: - **WHEN** a request is received without valid credentials\n229: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 401 Unauthorized\n230: \n231: ---\n232: \n233: ### Requirement: Request/Response Serialization\n234: \n235: The system SHALL properly serialize and deserialize JSON request and response bodies.\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: JSON request deserialization\n238: - **GIVEN** a POST request with `Content-Type: application/json`\n239: - **WHEN** the server receives the request body\n240: - **THEN** it SHALL deserialize the JSON into the appropriate Go struct\n241: \n242: #### Scenario: JSON response serialization\n243: - **GIVEN** a handler returns a Go struct\n244: - **WHEN** the server sends the response\n245: - **THEN** it SHALL serialize the struct to JSON with `Content-Type: application/json`\n246: \n247: #### Scenario: JSON field naming convention\n248: - **GIVEN** API response structs use camelCase JSON tags\n249: - **WHEN** responses are serialized\n250: - **THEN** field names SHALL follow camelCase convention (e.g., `createdAt`, `resourceVersion`)\n251: \n252: #### Scenario: Error response format\n253: - **GIVEN** an error occurs during request processing\n254: - **WHEN** the server returns an error response\n255: - **THEN** it SHALL return a JSON object with `error` and `message` fields (e.g., `{\"error\": \"NotFound\", \"message\": \"resource not found\"}`)\n256: \n257: ---\n258: \n259: ### Requirement: Query Parameter Support\n260: \n261: The system SHALL support standard Kubernetes-style query parameters for list operations.\n262: \n263: #### Scenario: Label selector filtering\n264: - **GIVEN** resources with various labels exist\n265: - **WHEN** a GET request is made with `?labelSelector=app=myapp`\n266: - **THEN** the server SHALL return only resources matching the label selector\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: Field selector filtering\n269: - **GIVEN** resources with various field values exist\n270: - **WHEN** a GET request is made with `?fieldSelector=spec.image=myimage`\n271: - **THEN** the server SHALL return only resources matching the field selector\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: Pagination with limit and continue\n274: - **GIVEN** more than 100 resources exist\n275: - **WHEN** a GET request is made with `?limit=10`\n276: - **THEN** the server SHALL return at most 10 items and include a `continue` token for pagination\n277: \n278: #### Scenario: Watch with resource version\n279: - **GIVEN** resources exist at resource version `12345`\n280: - **WHEN** a GET request is made with `?watch=true&resourceVersion=12345`\n281: - **THEN** the server SHALL start the watch from that resource version\n282: \n283: ---\n284: \n285: ### Requirement: Metrics and Observability\n286: \n287: The system SHALL expose Prometheus metrics for monitoring HTTP server performance.\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: HTTP request metrics\n290: - **GIVEN** the server is handling requests\n291: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n292: - **THEN** it SHALL expose `http_requests_total` counter with labels for method, path, and status\n293: \n294: #### Scenario: HTTP request duration metrics\n295: - **GIVEN** the server is handling requests\n296: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n297: - **THEN** it SHALL expose `http_request_duration_seconds` histogram with labels for method and path\n298: \n299: #### Scenario: Kubernetes client metrics\n300: - **GIVEN** the server is making Kubernetes API calls\n301: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n302: - **THEN** it SHALL expose `kubernetes_client_requests_total` counter for API operations\n303: \n304: #### Scenario: Resource operation metrics\n305: - **GIVEN** the server is processing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter operations\n306: - **WHEN** metrics endpoint `/metrics` is scraped\n307: - **THEN** it SHALL expose counters for create/update/delete operations by resource type\n308: \n309: ---\n310: \n311: ### Requirement: Structured Logging\n312: \n313: The system SHALL implement structured logging for all operations.\n314: \n315: #### Scenario: Request logging with fields\n316: - **GIVEN** a request is processed\n317: - **WHEN** the server logs the request\n318: - **THEN** it SHALL include structured fields: `method`, `path`, `status`, `duration`, `request_id`\n319: \n320: #### Scenario: Error logging with context\n321: - **GIVEN** an error occurs during API processing\n322: - **WHEN** the error is logged\n323: - **THEN** it SHALL include structured fields: `error`, `resource_type`, `resource_name`, `namespace`, `request_id`\n324: \n325: #### Scenario: Kubernetes API logging\n326: - **GIVEN** the server makes a Kubernetes API call\n327: - **WHEN** the operation is logged\n328: - **THEN** it SHALL include fields: `operation`, `resource`, `namespace`, `duration`, `error` (if any)\n329: \n330: #### Scenario: Configurable log level\n331: - **GIVEN** the `LOG_LEVEL` environment variable is set to `debug`\n332: - **WHEN** the server logs messages\n333: - **THEN** debug-level messages SHALL be output alongside info and error messages\n334: \n335: ---\n336: \n337: ### Requirement: Configuration Management\n338: \n339: The system SHALL support configuration via environment variables and configuration files.\n340: \n341: #### Scenario: Server configuration from environment variables\n342: - **GIVEN** environment variables `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_HOST`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_PORT`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_TLS_CERT`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_TLS_KEY`\n343: - **WHEN** the configuration is loaded\n344: - **THEN** it SHALL populate the server configuration struct with these values\n345: \n346: #### Scenario: Kubernetes configuration from environment\n347: - **GIVEN** environment variables `KUBECONFIG` or in-cluster configuration\n348: - **WHEN** the Kubernetes client configuration is loaded\n349: - **THEN** it SHALL use the specified kubeconfig or in-cluster settings\n350: \n351: #### Scenario: Redis configuration from environment\n352: - **GIVEN** environment variables `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD`\n353: - **WHEN** the Redis client configuration is loaded\n354: - **THEN** it SHALL populate the Redis connection configuration\n355: \n356: #### Scenario: Configuration validation\n357: - **GIVEN** an invalid configuration (e.g., invalid port number)\n358: - **WHEN** the configuration is loaded\n359: - **THEN** it SHALL return a validation error before starting the server\n360: \n361: ---\n362: \n363: ### Requirement: Error Handling\n364: \n365: The system SHALL implement consistent error handling across all endpoints.\n366: \n367: #### Scenario: Kubernetes API errors mapped to HTTP status\n368: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API call returns `apierrors.IsNotFound`\n369: - **WHEN** the error is processed\n370: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 404\n371: \n372: #### Scenario: Kubernetes API conflict mapped to HTTP 409\n373: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API call returns `apierrors.IsConflict`\n374: - **WHEN** the error is processed\n375: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 409 Conflict\n376: \n377: #### Scenario: Kubernetes API unauthorized mapped to HTTP 403\n378: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API call returns `apierrors.IsForbidden`\n379: - **WHEN** the error is processed\n380: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 403 Forbidden\n381: \n382: #### Scenario: Internal server errors mapped to HTTP 500\n383: - **GIVEN** an unexpected internal error occurs\n384: - **WHEN** the error is processed\n385: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 500 with a generic error message (details logged but not exposed)\n386: \n387: #### Scenario: Validation errors mapped to HTTP 400\n388: - **GIVEN** a request fails validation\n389: - **WHEN** the error is processed\n390: - **THEN** the server SHALL return HTTP 400 Bad Request with validation error details\n391: \n392: ---\n393: \n394: ### Requirement: Server Command Line Interface\n395: \n396: The system SHALL provide a CLI entry point for starting the WorkloadManager server.\n397: \n398: #### Scenario: Server starts with default configuration\n399: - **GIVEN** the `workloadmanager` binary is built\n400: - **WHEN** the operator runs `./bin/workloadmanager server`\n401: - **THEN** the server SHALL start with default configuration values\n402: \n403: #### Scenario: Server starts with flags\n404: - **GIVEN** command-line flags `--host=0.0.0.0 --port=9090 --tls-cert=/cert.pem --tls-key=/key.pem`\n405: - **WHEN** the operator runs `./bin/workloadmanager server` with these flags\n406: - **THEN** the server SHALL start with the specified configuration\n407: \n408: #### Scenario: Server shows help\n409: - **GIVEN** the operator wants to see available options\n410: - **WHEN** the operator runs `./bin/workloadmanager server --help`\n411: - **THEN** it SHALL display help text with all available flags and their descriptions\n412: \n413: #### Scenario: Server respects signal handling\n414: - **GIVEN** the server is running\n415: - **WHEN** the process receives SIGTERM or SIGINT\n416: - **THEN** the server SHALL initiate graceful shutdown with a configurable timeout\n417: \n418: ---\n419: \n420: ## File Index\n421: \n422: | Path | Purpose |\n423: |------|---------|\n424: | `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | Main entry point for the WorkloadManager binary |\n425: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server/server.go` | HTTP server bootstrap and lifecycle management |\n426: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server/config.go` | Server configuration structures and loading |\n427: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server/routes.go` | HTTP route definitions and handler registration |\n428: | `pkg/workloadmanager/server/middleware.go` | HTTP middleware implementations (logging, recovery, auth) |\n429: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/health.go` | Health and readiness endpoint handlers |\n430: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/agentruntime.go` | AgentRuntime CRUD endpoint handlers |\n431: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/codeinterpreter.go` | CodeInterpreter CRUD endpoint handlers |\n432: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/common.go` | Common handler utilities and response helpers |\n433: | `pkg/workloadmanager/client/kube.go` | Kubernetes client initialization and wrapper |\n434: | `pkg/workloadmanager/metrics/metrics.go` | Prometheus metrics definitions and recording |\n435: | `pkg/workloadmanager/logger/logger.go` | Structured logging configuration and helpers |\n436: \n437: ---\n438: \n439: ## Dependencies\n440: \n441: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n442: |------------|---------|---------|\n443: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Local | Generated Kubernetes clientset |\n444: | `k8s.io/client-go` | `v0.34.1` | Kubernetes REST client |\n445: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | Kubernetes API machinery |\n446: | `github.com/gorilla/mux` or `net/http` | Latest | HTTP routing |\n447: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | Latest | Prometheus metrics |\n448: | `github.com/sirupsen/logrus` or `slog` | Latest | Structured logging |\n449: | `github.com/rs/cors` | Latest | CORS middleware (optional) |\n450: \n451: ---\n452: \n453: ## API Endpoints Summary\n454: \n455: | Method | Path | Description |\n456: |--------|------|-------------|\n457: | GET | `/healthz` | Liveness probe |\n458: | GET | `/readyz` | Readiness probe |\n459: | GET | `/metrics` | Prometheus metrics |\n460: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes` | List AgentRuntimes |\n461: | POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes` | Create AgentRuntime |\n462: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Get AgentRuntime |\n463: | PUT | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Update AgentRuntime |\n464: | DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Delete AgentRuntime |\n465: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}/status` | Get AgentRuntime status |\n466: | PUT | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}/status` | Update AgentRuntime status |\n467: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | List CodeInterpreters |\n468: | POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | Create CodeInterpreter |\n469: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Get CodeInterpreter |\n470: | PUT | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Update CodeInterpreter |\n471: | DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Delete CodeInterpreter |\n472: | GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status` | Get CodeInterpreter status |\n473: | PUT | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}/status` | Update CodeInterpreter status |\n474: \n475: ---\n476: \n477: ## Notes\n478: \n479: - The WorkloadManager HTTP service serves as the control plane API for the AgentCube system\n480: - All endpoints that modify resources SHALL use the Kubernetes API server for persistence\n481: - The service SHALL be stateless, with all state stored in Kubernetes resources and Redis\n482: - The API follows RESTful conventions similar to the Kubernetes API for consistency\n483: - WebSocket or Server-Sent Events (SSE) may be used for the watch endpoints\n484: - The service SHALL support both in-cluster and external Kubernetes cluster configurations\n\n(End of file - total 484 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-004 — WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-004  \n**Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n\nEstablish the HTTP service framework for the WorkloadManager component, providing RESTful APIs for managing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, health endpoints, and integration with the Kubernetes client-go library.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: HTTP Server Bootstrap\n\nThe system SHALL provide a configurable HTTP server that can be started and gracefully shut down.\n\n#### Scenario: Server starts with configuration","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775875300351,"end":1775875300369}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875300376,"sessionID":"ses_28595af03ffeB1qczelYixQTBJ","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6a8fa70015X8n7hPvilN9NY","messageID":"msg_d7a6a793a001Dgbsfk6glSTl7n","sessionID":"ses_28595af03ffeB1qczelYixQTBJ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015 Design: PicoD Command Execution API\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-015  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** M (Medium)\n9: \n10: The PicoD Command Execution API provides a unified interface for executing commands within sandboxed environments in the agentcube platform. It supports both synchronous and asynchronous execution modes, resource constraint enforcement, output capture and streaming, and complete execution lifecycle management.\n11: \n12: This implementation integrates with:\n13: - **Sandbox Interface (AR-009)**: For actual command execution in sandbox environments\n14: - **Status Store (AR-012/AR-013/AR-014)**: For execution status persistence\n15: - **client-go Library**: For Kubernetes API interactions with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## Architecture\n20: \n21: ### High-Level Design\n22: \n23: ```\n24: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n25: │                         Client Applications                                  │\n26: │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐                         │\n27: │  │  Workload   │  │   CLI       │  │  Session    │                         │\n28: │  │  Manager    │  │   Toolkit   │  │  Manager    │                         │\n29: │  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘                         │\n30: └─────────┼────────────────┼────────────────┼────────────────────────────────┘\n31:           │                │                │\n32:           ▼                ▼                ▼\n33: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n34: │                    PicoD CommandExecutor API                                 │\n35: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n36: │  │                    CommandExecutor Interface                            │ │\n37: │  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────────┐ │ │\n38: │  │  │   Execute()     │  │  ExecuteAsync() │  │   GetStatus()          │ │ │\n39: │  │  │   · Synchronous │  │  · Queue exec   │  │   · Query status       │ │ │\n40: │  │  │   · Blocking    │  │  · Return ID    │  │   · State transitions  │ │ │\n41: │  │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └────────────────────────┘ │ │\n42: │  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐                             │ │\n43: │  │  │   Cancel()      │  │  StreamOutput() │                             │ │\n44: │  │  │   · Signal stop │  │  · Real-time    │                             │ │\n45: │  │  │   · Update state│  │  · Channel      │                             │ │\n46: │  │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘                             │ │\n47: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n48: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n49: │                    Execution Management Layer                                │\n50: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐  │\n51: │  │  ExecutionQueue  │  │  StatusManager   │  │  OutputBuffer            │  │\n52: │  │  · FIFO queue    │  │  · State machine │  │  · Circular buffer       │  │\n53: │  │  · Priority      │  │  · Persistence   │  │  · Size limits           │  │\n54: │  │  · Concurrency   │  │  · Transitions   │  │  · Streaming             │  │\n55: │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘  │\n56: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n57: │                    Sandbox Interface (AR-009)                                │\n58: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐  │\n59: │  │  Sandbox Resolver│  │  Command Runner  │  │  Resource Limiter        │  │\n60: │  │  · Session lookup│  │  · Execute cmd   │  │  · Memory limits         │  │\n61: │  │  · Connection    │  │  · Stream I/O    │  │  · CPU throttling        │  │\n62: │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘  │\n63: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n64: │                    Status Store (AR-012/13/14)                               │\n65: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐                                │\n66: │  │  Redis/Valkey    │  │  ExecutionStore  │                                │\n67: │  │  · Status cache  │  │  · CRUD ops      │                                │\n68: │  │  · TTL support   │  │  · Query         │                                │\n69: │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘                                │\n70: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n71: ```\n72: \n73: ### Component Architecture\n74: \n75: ```\n76: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n77: │                         Command Execution Flow                               │\n78: │                                                                              │\n79: │  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n80: │  │  Client  │──▶│  Execute │──▶│ Validate │──▶│ Generate │──▶│  Check   │  │\n81: │  │  Request │   │  Method  │   │  Request │   │    ID    │   │  Sandbox │  │\n82: │  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └────┬─────┘  │\n83: │                                                                    │        │\n84: │                              ┌─────────────────────────────────────┘        │\n85: │                              ▼                                              │\n86: │  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n87: │  │  Return  │◀──│  Capture │◀──│  Execute │◀──│  Prepare │◀──│  Resolve │  │\n88: │  │  Result  │   │  Output  │   │  Command │   │  Sandbox │   │  Sandbox │  │\n89: │  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘  │\n90: │                                                                              │\n91: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n92: ```\n93: \n94: ### Component Interactions\n95: \n96: | Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n97: |-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n98: | **CommandExecutor** | Primary API for command execution | `ExecutionRequest`, `ExecutionID` | `ExecutionResult`, `ExecutionStatus`, error |\n99: | **RequestValidator** | Validates execution requests | `ExecutionRequest` | Error or nil |\n100: | **ExecutionQueue** | Manages async execution queue | `ExecutionRequest` | `ExecutionID` |\n101: | **StatusManager** | Tracks and persists execution state | State transitions | Updated `ExecutionStatus` |\n102: | **OutputBuffer** | Captures and buffers command output | Output streams | `OutputChunk` channel |\n103: | **SandboxResolver** | Resolves session to sandbox | `SessionID` | `SandboxInfo` |\n104: | **ResourceLimiter** | Enforces resource constraints | `ResourceConstraints` | Enforced limits |\n105: | **ExecutionStore** | Persists execution metadata | `ExecutionStatus` | Stored status |\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ## Directory Structure\n110: \n111: ```\n112: pkg/picod/\n113: ├── executor.go              # CommandExecutor interface and implementation (~250 lines)\n114: ├── types.go                 # ExecutionRequest, ExecutionResult, ExecutionStatus (~100 lines)\n115: ├── status.go                # Status management and state transitions (~80 lines)\n116: ├── output.go                # Output capture and streaming (~120 lines)\n117: ├── errors.go                # Error type definitions (~50 lines)\n118: ├── validation.go            # Request validation logic (~80 lines)\n119: ├── config.go                # Configuration and defaults (~60 lines)\n120: └── executor_test.go         # Unit tests (~200 lines)\n121: ```\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ## Data Structures\n126: \n127: ### Request DTOs\n128: \n129: #### ExecutionRequest\n130: \n131: ```go\n132: // ExecutionRequest contains parameters for command execution.\n133: type ExecutionRequest struct {\n134:     // Command is the command to execute (required)\n135:     Command string `json:\"command\" validate:\"required\"`\n136: \n137:     // Args are the command arguments\n138:     Args []string `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n139: \n140:     // WorkingDir is the working directory for execution (default: sandbox default)\n141:     WorkingDir string `json:\"workingDir,omitempty\"`\n142: \n143:     // Environment defines environment variables (merged with sandbox defaults)\n144:     Environment map[string]string `json:\"environment,omitempty\"`\n145: \n146:     // Timeout is the maximum execution time (default: 30s)\n147:     Timeout time.Duration `json:\"timeout,omitempty\"`\n148: \n149:     // ResourceLimits defines resource constraints for execution\n150:     ResourceLimits ResourceConstraints `json:\"resourceLimits,omitempty\"`\n151: \n152:     // SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n153:     SessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n154: }\n155: \n156: // Validate validates the execution request.\n157: func (r *ExecutionRequest) Validate() error {\n158:     if strings.TrimSpace(r.Command) == \"\" {\n159:         return ErrInvalidCommand\n160:     }\n161:     if strings.Contains(r.Command, \"..\") || strings.Contains(r.Command, \"//\") {\n162:         return fmt.Errorf(\"%w: command contains invalid characters\", ErrInvalidCommand)\n163:     }\n164:     if r.SessionID == \"\" {\n165:         return ErrInvalidSessionID\n166:     }\n167:     if r.WorkingDir != \"\" && !isAllowedWorkingDir(r.WorkingDir) {\n168:         return ErrInvalidWorkingDir\n169:     }\n170:     for name := range r.Environment {\n171:         if !isValidEnvVarName(name) {\n172:             return fmt.Errorf(\"%w: invalid environment variable name: %s\", ErrInvalidRequest, name)\n173:         }\n174:     }\n175:     return nil\n176: }\n177: ```\n178: \n179: ### Response DTOs\n180: \n181: #### ExecutionResult\n182: \n183: ```go\n184: // ExecutionResult contains the result of a command execution.\n185: type ExecutionResult struct {\n186:     // ID is the unique execution identifier\n187:     ID ExecutionID `json:\"id\"`\n188: \n189:     // Status contains the execution status details\n190:     Status ExecutionStatus `json:\"status\"`\n191: \n192:     // ExitCode is the command exit code (0 for success)\n193:     ExitCode int `json:\"exitCode\"`\n194: \n195:     // Stdout contains the captured standard output\n196:     Stdout []byte `json:\"stdout,omitempty\"`\n197: \n198:     // Stderr contains the captured standard error\n199:     Stderr []byte `json:\"stderr,omitempty\"`\n200: \n201:     // StartedAt is when execution started\n202:     StartedAt time.Time `json:\"startedAt\"`\n203: \n204:     // FinishedAt is when execution completed\n205:     FinishedAt time.Time `json:\"finishedAt\"`\n206: \n207:     // Error contains error details if execution failed\n208:     Error *ExecutionError `json:\"error,omitempty\"`\n209: \n210:     // Truncated indicates if output was truncated due to size limits\n211:     Truncated bool `json:\"truncated,omitempty\"`\n212: }\n213: \n214: // ExecutionError contains detailed error information.\n215: type ExecutionError struct {\n216:     // Code is the machine-readable error code\n217:     Code string `json:\"code\"`\n218: \n219:     // Message is the human-readable error message\n220:     Message string `json:\"message\"`\n221: \n222:     // Details contains additional error context\n223:     Details map[string]interface{} `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n224: }\n225: ```\n226: \n227: #### ExecutionStatus\n228: \n229: ```go\n230: // ExecutionStatus represents the current state of an execution.\n231: type ExecutionStatus struct {\n232:     // ID is the unique execution identifier\n233:     ID ExecutionID `json:\"id\"`\n234: \n235:     // State is the current execution state\n236:     State ExecutionState `json:\"state\"`\n237: \n238:     // StartedAt is when execution started (nil if not started)\n239:     StartedAt *time.Time `json:\"startedAt,omitempty\"`\n240: \n241:     // FinishedAt is when execution completed (nil if not finished)\n242:     FinishedAt *time.Time `json:\"finishedAt,omitempty\"`\n243: \n244:     // ExitCode is the command exit code (nil if not finished)\n245:     ExitCode *int `json:\"exitCode,omitempty\"`\n246: \n247:     // OutputRef references stored output (for large outputs)\n248:     OutputRef string `json:\"outputRef,omitempty\"`\n249: }\n250: \n251: // ExecutionState represents the state of command execution.\n252: type ExecutionState string\n253: \n254: const (\n255:     // StatePending indicates the execution is queued\n256:     StatePending ExecutionState = \"pending\"\n257: \n258:     // StateRunning indicates the execution is in progress\n259:     StateRunning ExecutionState = \"running\"\n260: \n261:     // StateCompleted indicates the execution completed successfully\n262:     StateCompleted ExecutionState = \"completed\"\n263: \n264:     // StateFailed indicates the execution failed\n265:     StateFailed ExecutionState = \"failed\"\n266: \n267:     // StateCancelled indicates the execution was cancelled\n268:     StateCancelled ExecutionState = \"cancelled\"\n269: )\n270: \n271: // IsTerminal returns true if the state is terminal (completed, failed, or cancelled).\n272: func (s ExecutionState) IsTerminal() bool {\n273:     return s == StateCompleted || s == StateFailed || s == StateCancelled\n274: }\n275: ```\n276: \n277: ### Domain Types\n278: \n279: #### ResourceConstraints\n280: \n281: ```go\n282: // ResourceConstraints defines resource limits for execution.\n283: type ResourceConstraints struct {\n284:     // MaxMemory is the maximum memory in bytes (0 = unlimited)\n285:     MaxMemory int64 `json:\"maxMemory,omitempty\"`\n286: \n287:     // MaxCPU is the maximum CPU percentage (0-100, 0 = unlimited)\n288:     MaxCPU float64 `json:\"maxCpu,omitempty\"`\n289: \n290:     // MaxIOBytes is the maximum IO bandwidth in bytes per second (0 = unlimited)\n291:     MaxIOBytes int64 `json:\"maxIoBytes,omitempty\"`\n292: \n293:     // MaxFiles is the maximum number of open file descriptors (0 = unlimited)\n294:     MaxFiles int `json:\"maxFiles,omitempty\"`\n295: }\n296: \n297: // IsEmpty returns true if no constraints are set.\n298: func (r ResourceConstraints) IsEmpty() bool {\n299:     return r.MaxMemory == 0 && r.MaxCPU == 0 && r.MaxIOBytes == 0 && r.MaxFiles == 0\n300: }\n301: \n302: // Validate validates resource constraints.\n303: func (r ResourceConstraints) Validate() error {\n304:     if r.MaxMemory < 0 {\n305:         return fmt.Errorf(\"%w: maxMemory cannot be negative\", ErrInvalidRequest)\n306:     }\n307:     if r.MaxCPU < 0 || r.MaxCPU > 100 {\n308:         return fmt.Errorf(\"%w: maxCpu must be between 0 and 100\", ErrInvalidRequest)\n309:     }\n310:     if r.MaxIOBytes < 0 {\n311:         return fmt.Errorf(\"%w: maxIoBytes cannot be negative\", ErrInvalidRequest)\n312:     }\n313:     if r.MaxFiles < 0 {\n314:         return fmt.Errorf(\"%w: maxFiles cannot be negative\", ErrInvalidRequest)\n315:     }\n316:     return nil\n317: }\n318: ```\n319: \n320: #### OutputChunk\n321: \n322: ```go\n323: // OutputChunk represents a piece of output from a command.\n324: type OutputChunk struct {\n325:     // Data is the output data\n326:     Data []byte `json:\"data\"`\n327: \n328:     // Type indicates the output source\n329:     Type OutputType `json:\"type\"`\n330: \n331:     // Timestamp is when the output was captured\n332:     Timestamp time.Time `json:\"timestamp\"`\n333: }\n334: \n335: // OutputType indicates the source of output.\n336: type OutputType string\n337: \n338: const (\n339:     // Stdout indicates standard output\n340:     Stdout OutputType = \"stdout\"\n341: \n342:     // Stderr indicates standard error\n343:     Stderr OutputType = \"stderr\"\n344: )\n345: ```\n346: \n347: ### Internal Types\n348: \n349: #### CommandExecutor\n350: \n351: ```go\n352: // ExecutionID uniquely identifies a command execution.\n353: type ExecutionID string\n354: \n355: // CommandExecutor defines the interface for executing commands in sandboxes.\n356: type CommandExecutor interface {\n357:     // Execute runs a command synchronously and returns the result.\n358:     // Blocks until execution completes, times out, or is cancelled.\n359:     Execute(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (*ExecutionResult, error)\n360: \n361:     // ExecuteAsync runs a command asynchronously and returns an execution ID.\n362:     // Returns immediately; use GetStatus to poll for completion.\n363:     ExecuteAsync(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (ExecutionID, error)\n364: \n365:     // GetStatus retrieves the current status of an execution.\n366:     // Returns ErrExecutionNotFound if the execution does not exist.\n367:     GetStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (*ExecutionStatus, error)\n368: \n369:     // Cancel stops a running execution.\n370:     // Returns ErrExecutionAlreadyComplete if execution is in terminal state.\n371:     Cancel(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) error\n372: \n373:     // StreamOutput returns a channel for streaming output from an execution.\n374:     // Channel is closed when execution completes or context is cancelled.\n375:     StreamOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (<-chan OutputChunk, error)\n376: }\n377: \n378: // executor implements CommandExecutor.\n379: type executor struct {\n380:     // store persists execution status\n381:     store ExecutionStore\n382: \n383:     // sandboxResolver resolves session IDs to sandbox info\n384:     sandboxResolver SandboxResolver\n385: \n386:     // queue manages async execution queue\n387:     queue ExecutionQueue\n388: \n389:     // config contains executor configuration\n390:     config ExecutorConfig\n391: \n392:     // outputBuffers stores output buffers by execution ID\n393:     outputBuffers map[ExecutionID]*OutputBuffer\n394: \n395:     // mu protects outputBuffers\n396:     mu sync.RWMutex\n397: \n398:     // ctx is the executor context for background workers\n399:     ctx context.Context\n400: \n401:     // cancel cancels the executor context\n402:     cancel context.CancelFunc\n403: }\n404: ```\n405: \n406: #### ExecutionStore\n407: \n408: ```go\n409: // ExecutionStore defines the interface for execution status persistence.\n410: type ExecutionStore interface {\n411:     // CreateStatus creates a new execution status record.\n412:     CreateStatus(ctx context.Context, status *ExecutionStatus) error\n413: \n414:     // GetStatus retrieves execution status by ID.\n415:     // Returns ErrExecutionNotFound if not found.\n416:     GetStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (*ExecutionStatus, error)\n417: \n418:     // UpdateStatus updates execution status.\n419:     UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, status *ExecutionStatus) error\n420: \n421:     // UpdateStatusWithTransition updates status with state transition validation.\n422:     // Only allows valid state transitions.\n423:     UpdateStatusWithTransition(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID, from, to ExecutionState, updateFn func(*ExecutionStatus)) error\n424: \n425:     // DeleteStatus removes an execution status record.\n426:     DeleteStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) error\n427: \n428:     // ListExecutions lists executions filtered by state and session.\n429:     ListExecutions(ctx context.Context, filter ExecutionFilter) ([]*ExecutionStatus, error)\n430: \n431:     // StoreOutput stores execution output for later retrieval.\n432:     StoreOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID, stdout, stderr []byte) error\n433: \n434:     // GetOutput retrieves stored execution output.\n435:     GetOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (stdout, stderr []byte, err error)\n436: }\n437: \n438: // ExecutionFilter defines filters for listing executions.\n439: type ExecutionFilter struct {\n440:     // SessionID filters by session\n441:     SessionID string\n442: \n443:     // State filters by execution state\n444:     State ExecutionState\n445: \n446:     // Limit limits the number of results\n447:     Limit int\n448: }\n449: ```\n450: \n451: #### ExecutionQueue\n452: \n453: ```go\n454: // ExecutionQueue manages the async execution queue.\n455: type ExecutionQueue interface {\n456:     // Enqueue adds an execution request to the queue.\n457:     // Returns the assigned execution ID.\n458:     Enqueue(req ExecutionRequest) (ExecutionID, error)\n459: \n460:     // Dequeue retrieves the next pending execution.\n461:     // Blocks until an execution is available or context is cancelled.\n462:     Dequeue(ctx context.Context) (*QueuedExecution, error)\n463: \n464:     // GetPosition returns the queue position for an execution.\n465:     GetPosition(id ExecutionID) (int, error)\n466: \n467:     // Remove removes an execution from the queue.\n468:     Remove(id ExecutionID) error\n469: \n470:     // Size returns the current queue size.\n471:     Size() int\n472: }\n473: \n474: // QueuedExecution represents an execution in the queue.\n475: type QueuedExecution struct {\n476:     ID      ExecutionID\n477:     Request ExecutionRequest\n478:     EnqueuedAt time.Time\n479: }\n480: \n481: // executionQueue implements ExecutionQueue.\n482: type executionQueue struct {\n483:     // items is the ordered queue of executions\n484:     items []*QueuedExecution\n485: \n486:     // mu protects items\n487:     mu sync.RWMutex\n488: \n489:     // cond signals when items are added\n490:     cond *sync.Cond\n491: \n492:     // idGen generates unique IDs\n493:     idGen func() ExecutionID\n494: }\n495: ```\n496: \n497: #### OutputBuffer\n498: \n499: ```go\n500: // OutputBuffer provides circular buffer for command output.\n501: type OutputBuffer struct {\n502:     // id is the execution ID\n503:     id ExecutionID\n504: \n505:     // buffer is the circular buffer for output\n506:     buffer *ring.Ring\n507: \n508:     // mu protects buffer\n509:     mu sync.RWMutex\n510: \n511:     // subscribers are channels to broadcast output to\n512:     subscribers []chan OutputChunk\n513: \n514:     // subMu protects subscribers\n515:     subMu sync.RWMutex\n516: \n517:     // closed indicates if the buffer is closed\n518:     closed bool\n519: \n520:     // maxSize is the maximum buffer size\n521:     maxSize int\n522: }\n523: \n524: // NewOutputBuffer creates a new output buffer.\n525: func NewOutputBuffer(id ExecutionID, maxSize int) *OutputBuffer {\n526:     return &OutputBuffer{\n527:         id:      id,\n528:         buffer:  ring.New(maxSize),\n529:         maxSize: maxSize,\n530:     }\n531: }\n532: \n533: // Write writes output to the buffer.\n534: func (b *OutputBuffer) Write(data []byte, typ OutputType) {\n535:     b.mu.Lock()\n536:     defer b.mu.Unlock()\n537: \n538:     if b.closed {\n539:         return\n540:     }\n541: \n542:     chunk := OutputChunk{\n543:         Data:      data,\n544:         Type:      typ,\n545:         Timestamp: time.Now(),\n546:     }\n547: \n548:     b.buffer.Value = chunk\n549:     b.buffer = b.buffer.Next()\n550: \n551:     // Broadcast to subscribers\n552:     b.broadcast(chunk)\n553: }\n554: \n555: // Subscribe returns a channel for receiving output chunks.\n556: func (b *OutputBuffer) Subscribe() <-chan OutputChunk {\n557:     b.subMu.Lock()\n558:     defer b.subMu.Unlock()\n559: \n560:     ch := make(chan OutputChunk, 100)\n561:     b.subscribers = append(b.subscribers, ch)\n562: \n563:     // Send buffered output to new subscriber\n564:     b.mu.RLock()\n565:     b.buffer.Do(func(v interface{}) {\n566:         if v != nil {\n567:             select {\n568:             case ch <- v.(OutputChunk):\n569:             default:\n570:             }\n571:         }\n572:     })\n573:     b.mu.RUnlock()\n574: \n575:     return ch\n576: }\n577: \n578: // Close closes the buffer and all subscriber channels.\n579: func (b *OutputBuffer) Close() {\n580:     b.mu.Lock()\n581:     b.closed = true\n582:     b.mu.Unlock()\n583: \n584:     b.subMu.Lock()\n585:     for _, ch := range b.subscribers {\n586:         close(ch)\n587:     }\n588:     b.subscribers = nil\n589:     b.subMu.Unlock()\n590: }\n591: ```\n592: \n593: #### ExecutorConfig\n594: \n595: ```go\n596: // ExecutorConfig contains configuration for CommandExecutor.\n597: type ExecutorConfig struct {\n598:     // DefaultTimeout is the default execution timeout\n599:     DefaultTimeout time.Duration\n600: \n601:     // MaxConcurrentExecutions limits concurrent executions\n602:     MaxConcurrentExecutions int\n603: \n604:     // MaxOutputSize is the maximum output capture size\n605:     MaxOutputSize int64\n606: \n607:     // OutputBufferSize is the output buffer size for streaming\n608:     OutputBufferSize int\n609: \n610:     // MaxExecutionQueueSize limits the async queue size\n611:     MaxExecutionQueueSize int\n612: \n613:     // ExecutionTTL is how long to retain execution records\n614:     ExecutionTTL time.Duration\n615: }\n616: \n617: // DefaultConfig returns the default executor configuration.\n618: func DefaultConfig() ExecutorConfig {\n619:     return ExecutorConfig{\n620:         DefaultTimeout:          30 * time.Second,\n621:         MaxConcurrentExecutions: 100,\n622:         MaxOutputSize:           10 * 1024 * 1024, // 10MB\n623:         OutputBufferSize:        4 * 1024,          // 4KB\n624:         MaxExecutionQueueSize:   1000,\n625:         ExecutionTTL:            24 * time.Hour,\n626:     }\n627: }\n628: \n629: // ConfigFromEnv loads configuration from environment variables.\n630: func ConfigFromEnv() ExecutorConfig {\n631:     cfg := DefaultConfig()\n632: \n633:     if v := os.Getenv(\"PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT\"); v != \"\" {\n634:         if d, err := time.ParseDuration(v); err == nil {\n635:             cfg.DefaultTimeout = d\n636:         }\n637:     }\n638:     if v := os.Getenv(\"PICOD_MAX_CONCURRENT\"); v != \"\" {\n639:         if n, err := strconv.Atoi(v); err == nil {\n640:             cfg.MaxConcurrentExecutions = n\n641:         }\n642:     }\n643:     if v := os.Getenv(\"PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE\"); v != \"\" {\n644:         if n, err := strconv.ParseInt(v, 10, 64); err == nil {\n645:             cfg.MaxOutputSize = n\n646:         }\n647:     }\n648:     if v := os.Getenv(\"PICOD_OUTPUT_BUFFER_SIZE\"); v != \"\" {\n649:         if n, err := strconv.Atoi(v); err == nil {\n650:             cfg.OutputBufferSize = n\n651:         }\n652:     }\n653: \n654:     return cfg\n655: }\n656: ```\n657: \n658: ### Constants\n659: \n660: ```go\n661: // Default configuration values\n662: const (\n663:     // DefaultTimeout is the default execution timeout (30 seconds)\n664:     DefaultTimeout = 30 * time.Second\n665: \n666:     // DefaultMaxConcurrent is the default concurrent execution limit\n667:     DefaultMaxConcurrent = 100\n668: \n669:     // DefaultMaxOutputSize is the default max output size (10MB)\n670:     DefaultMaxOutputSize = 10 * 1024 * 1024\n671: \n672:     // DefaultOutputBufferSize is the default output buffer size (4KB)\n673:     DefaultOutputBufferSize = 4 * 1024\n674: \n675:     // ExecutionIDLength is the length of generated execution IDs\n676:     ExecutionIDLength = 16\n677: \n678:     // ExecutionIDPrefix is the prefix for execution IDs\n679:     ExecutionIDPrefix = \"exec-\"\n680: )\n681: \n682: // Error codes\n683: const (\n684:     // ErrorCodeInvalidRequest indicates malformed request\n685:     ErrorCodeInvalidRequest = \"INVALID_REQUEST\"\n686: \n687:     // ErrorCodeInvalidCommand indicates empty or invalid command\n688:     ErrorCodeInvalidCommand = \"INVALID_COMMAND\"\n689: \n690:     // ErrorCodeInvalidSessionID indicates missing or invalid session ID\n691:     ErrorCodeInvalidSessionID = \"INVALID_SESSION_ID\"\n692: \n693:     // ErrorCodeInvalidWorkingDir indicates invalid working directory\n694:     ErrorCodeInvalidWorkingDir = \"INVALID_WORKING_DIR\"\n695: \n696:     // ErrorCodeResourceExceeded indicates resource limits exceeded\n697:     ErrorCodeResourceExceeded = \"RESOURCE_EXCEEDED\"\n698: \n699:     // ErrorCodeTimeout indicates execution timeout\n700:     ErrorCodeTimeout = \"TIMEOUT\"\n701: \n702:     // ErrorCodeSandboxUnavailable indicates sandbox not accessible\n703:     ErrorCodeSandboxUnavailable = \"SANDBOX_UNAVAILABLE\"\n704: \n705:     // ErrorCodeExecutionFailed indicates command returned non-zero exit\n706:     ErrorCodeExecutionFailed = \"EXECUTION_FAILED\"\n707: \n708:     // ErrorCodeExecutionNotFound indicates execution ID not found\n709:     ErrorCodeExecutionNotFound = \"EXECUTION_NOT_FOUND\"\n710: \n711:     // ErrorCodeExecutionAlreadyComplete indicates cannot cancel completed execution\n712:     ErrorCodeExecutionAlreadyComplete = \"EXECUTION_ALREADY_COMPLETE\"\n713: \n714:     // ErrorCodeTooManyConcurrent indicates concurrent limit exceeded\n715:     ErrorCodeTooManyConcurrent = \"TOO_MANY_CONCURRENT\"\n716: \n717:     // ErrorCodeCancelled indicates execution was cancelled\n718:     ErrorCodeCancelled = \"CANCELLED\"\n719: )\n720: ```\n721: \n722: ---\n723: \n724: ## API Contracts\n725: \n726: ### CommandExecutor Interface\n727: \n728: ```go\n729: // CommandExecutor is the primary API for PicoD command execution.\n730: type CommandExecutor interface {\n731:     // Execute runs a command synchronously and returns the result.\n732:     //\n733:     // Parameters:\n734:     //   - ctx: Context for cancellation and timeouts\n735:     //   - req: Execution request containing command, args, and options\n736:     //\n737:     // Returns:\n738:     //   - *ExecutionResult: Result containing exit code, output, and timing\n739:     //   - error: ErrInvalidRequest, ErrTimeout, ErrSandboxUnavailable, etc.\n740:     Execute(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (*ExecutionResult, error)\n741: \n742:     // ExecuteAsync runs a command asynchronously and returns an execution ID.\n743:     //\n744:     // Parameters:\n745:     //   - ctx: Context for the enqueue operation\n746:     //   - req: Execution request\n747:     //\n748:     // Returns:\n749:     //   - ExecutionID: Unique identifier for tracking the execution\n750:     //   - error: ErrInvalidRequest, ErrTooManyConcurrent, etc.\n751:     ExecuteAsync(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (ExecutionID, error)\n752: \n753:     // GetStatus retrieves the current status of an execution.\n754:     //\n755:     // Parameters:\n756:     //   - ctx: Context for the operation\n757:     //   - id: Execution identifier\n758:     //\n759:     // Returns:\n760:     //   - *ExecutionStatus: Current execution status\n761:     //   - error: ErrExecutionNotFound\n762:     GetStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (*ExecutionStatus, error)\n763: \n764:     // Cancel stops a running execution.\n765:     //\n766:     // Parameters:\n767:     //   - ctx: Context for the operation\n768:     //   - id: Execution identifier\n769:     //\n770:     // Returns:\n771:     //   - error: nil on success, ErrExecutionNotFound, ErrExecutionAlreadyComplete\n772:     Cancel(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) error\n773: \n774:     // StreamOutput returns a channel for streaming output from an execution.\n775:     //\n776:     // Parameters:\n777:     //   - ctx: Context for the streaming operation\n778:     //   - id: Execution identifier\n779:     //\n780:     // Returns:\n781:     //   - <-chan OutputChunk: Channel receiving output chunks\n782:     //   - error: ErrExecutionNotFound\n783:     StreamOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (<-chan OutputChunk, error)\n784: }\n785: ```\n786: \n787: ### Execution State Transitions\n788: \n789: ```\n790:                     ┌─────────────┐\n791:          ┌─────────▶│   Pending   │◀────────┐\n792:          │          │  (queued)   │         │\n793:          │          └──────┬──────┘         │\n794:          │                 │ dequeue        │ enqueue\n795:          │                 ▼                │\n796:          │          ┌─────────────┐         │\n797:          │          │   Running   │─────────┤\n798:          │          │ (executing) │         │\n799:          │          └──────┬──────┘         │\n800:          │                 │                │\n801:     cancel│         ┌──────┼──────┐         │\n802:          │         ▼      ▼      ▼         │\n803:          │    ┌────────┐ ┌────────┐ ┌──────────┐\n804:          └───▶│Failed  │ │Completed│ │Cancelled │\n805:               │(error) │ │(success)│ │(stopped) │\n806:               └────────┘ └────────┘ └──────────┘\n807: ```\n808: \n809: **Valid Transitions:**\n810: - `pending` → `running` (when dequeued and started)\n811: - `pending` → `cancelled` (if cancelled before start)\n812: - `running` → `completed` (on successful exit)\n813: - `running` → `failed` (on non-zero exit or error)\n814: - `running` → `cancelled` (on cancellation)\n815: \n816: ### Service Interface\n817: \n818: ```go\n819: // SandboxResolver resolves session IDs to sandbox information.\n820: type SandboxResolver interface {\n821:     // Resolve returns sandbox info for a session ID.\n822:     // Returns ErrSandboxNotFound if session doesn't exist.\n823:     Resolve(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n824: }\n825: \n826: // SandboxRunner executes commands in a sandbox.\n827: type SandboxRunner interface {\n828:     // Run executes a command synchronously.\n829:     Run(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, req ExecutionRequest) (*ExecutionResult, error)\n830: \n831:     // Start begins async command execution.\n832:     Start(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, req ExecutionRequest) error\n833: \n834:     // Cancel stops a running command.\n835:     Cancel(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, id ExecutionID) error\n836: }\n837: \n838: // PicoDService provides high-level PicoD operations.\n839: type PicoDService interface {\n840:     // CommandExecutor returns the command executor.\n841:     CommandExecutor() CommandExecutor\n842: \n843:     // Health returns the service health status.\n844:     Health(ctx context.Context) error\n845: \n846:     // Shutdown gracefully shuts down the service.\n847:     Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n848: }\n849: ```\n850: \n851: ---\n852: \n853: ## Error Handling\n854: \n855: ### Error Categories and Codes\n856: \n857: | Error | Code | Description | Retryable | Handling Strategy |\n858: |-------|------|-------------|-----------|-------------------|\n859: | `ErrInvalidRequest` | `INVALID_REQUEST` | Malformed execution request | No | Return with field details |\n860: | `ErrInvalidCommand` | `INVALID_COMMAND` | Empty or invalid command | No | Return with command details |\n861: | `ErrInvalidSessionID` | `INVALID_SESSION_ID` | Missing session ID | No | Return 400 |\n862: | `ErrInvalidWorkingDir` | `INVALID_WORKING_DIR` | Invalid working directory | No | Return 400 |\n863: | `ErrResourceExceeded` | `RESOURCE_EXCEEDED` | Resource limits exceeded | Yes | Retry with lower limits |\n864: | `ErrTimeout` | `TIMEOUT` | Execution exceeded timeout | Yes | Retry with longer timeout |\n865: | `ErrSandboxUnavailable` | `SANDBOX_UNAVAILABLE` | Sandbox not accessible | Yes | Retry with backoff |\n866: | `ErrExecutionFailed` | `EXECUTION_FAILED` | Command returned non-zero | No | Return with exit code |\n867: | `ErrExecutionNotFound` | `EXECUTION_NOT_FOUND` | Execution ID not found | No | Return 404 |\n868: | `ErrExecutionAlreadyComplete` | `EXECUTION_ALREADY_COMPLETE` | Cannot cancel completed | No | Return 409 |\n869: | `ErrTooManyConcurrent` | `TOO_MANY_CONCURRENT` | Concurrent limit exceeded | Yes | Queue or return 429 |\n870: | `ErrCancelled` | `CANCELLED` | Execution was cancelled | No | Return cancellation status |\n871: \n872: ### Sentinel Errors\n873: \n874: ```go\n875: // PicoD execution errors\n876: var (\n877:     ErrInvalidRequest              = errors.New(\"picod: invalid request\")\n878:     ErrInvalidCommand              = errors.New(\"picod: command is required\")\n879:     ErrInvalidSessionID            = errors.New(\"picod: session ID is required\")\n880:     ErrInvalidWorkingDir           = errors.New(\"picod: invalid working directory\")\n881:     ErrResourceExceeded            = errors.New(\"picod: resource limits exceeded\")\n882:     ErrTimeout                     = errors.New(\"picod: execution timeout\")\n883:     ErrSandboxUnavailable          = errors.New(\"picod: sandbox unavailable\")\n884:     ErrExecutionFailed             = errors.New(\"picod: execution failed\")\n885:     ErrExecutionNotFound           = errors.New(\"picod: execution not found\")\n886:     ErrExecutionAlreadyComplete    = errors.New(\"picod: execution already complete\")\n887:     ErrTooManyConcurrentExecutions = errors.New(\"picod: too many concurrent executions\")\n888:     ErrCancelled                   = errors.New(\"picod: execution cancelled\")\n889: )\n890: ```\n891: \n892: ### Error Handling Patterns\n893: \n894: #### Executor-Level Error Handling\n895: \n896: ```go\n897: func (e *executor) Execute(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (*ExecutionResult, error) {\n898:     // Validate request\n899:     if err := req.Validate(); err != nil {\n900:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrInvalidRequest, err)\n901:     }\n902: \n903:     // Apply default timeout\n904:     if req.Timeout == 0 {\n905:         req.Timeout = e.config.DefaultTimeout\n906:     }\n907: \n908:     // Check concurrent limit\n909:     if !e.acquireExecutionSlot(ctx) {\n910:         return nil, ErrTooManyConcurrentExecutions\n911:     }\n912:     defer e.releaseExecutionSlot()\n913: \n914:     // Resolve sandbox\n915:     sandbox, err := e.sandboxResolver.Resolve(ctx, req.SessionID)\n916:     if err != nil {\n917:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrSandboxUnavailable, err)\n918:     }\n919: \n920:     // Execute with timeout context\n921:     execCtx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, req.Timeout)\n922:     defer cancel()\n923: \n924:     result, err := e.runCommand(execCtx, sandbox, req)\n925:     if err != nil {\n926:         if errors.Is(err, context.DeadlineExceeded) {\n927:             return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: execution exceeded %v\", ErrTimeout, req.Timeout)\n928:         }\n929:         if errors.Is(err, context.Canceled) {\n930:             return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: execution was cancelled\", ErrCancelled)\n931:         }\n932:         return nil, err\n933:     }\n934: \n935:     return result, nil\n936: }\n937: ```\n938: \n939: #### State Transition Error Handling\n940: \n941: ```go\n942: func (s *executionStore) UpdateStatusWithTransition(\n943:     ctx context.Context,\n944:     id ExecutionID,\n945:     from, to ExecutionState,\n946:     updateFn func(*ExecutionStatus),\n947: ) error {\n948:     // Validate state transition\n949:     if !isValidTransition(from, to) {\n950:         return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid state transition from %s to %s\", from, to)\n951:     }\n952: \n953:     // Get current status\n954:     status, err := s.GetStatus(ctx, id)\n955:     if err != nil {\n956:         return err\n957:     }\n958: \n959:     // Check current state matches expected\n960:     if status.State != from {\n961:         return fmt.Errorf(\"execution %s is in state %s, expected %s\", id, status.State, from)\n962:     }\n963: \n964:     // Check if already in terminal state\n965:     if status.State.IsTerminal() {\n966:         return fmt.Errorf(\"%w: execution is in terminal state %s\", ErrExecutionAlreadyComplete, status.State)\n967:     }\n968: \n969:     // Apply update\n970:     status.State = to\n971:     if updateFn != nil {\n972:         updateFn(status)\n973:     }\n974: \n975:     // Persist\n976:     return s.UpdateStatus(ctx, status)\n977: }\n978: \n979: func isValidTransition(from, to ExecutionState) bool {\n980:     transitions := map[ExecutionState][]ExecutionState{\n981:         StatePending:   {StateRunning, StateCancelled},\n982:         StateRunning:   {StateCompleted, StateFailed, StateCancelled},\n983:         StateCompleted: {},\n984:         StateFailed:    {},\n985:         StateCancelled: {},\n986:     }\n987:     valid, ok := transitions[from]\n988:     if !ok {\n989:         return false\n990:     }\n991:     for _, s := range valid {\n992:         if s == to {\n993:             return true\n994:         }\n995:     }\n996:     return false\n997: }\n998: ```\n999: \n1000: #### Concurrent Execution Management\n1001: \n1002: ```go\n1003: func (e *executor) acquireExecutionSlot(ctx context.Context) bool {\n1004:     select {\n1005:     case e.executionSem <- struct{}{}:\n1006:         return true\n1007:     case <-ctx.Done():\n1008:         return false\n1009:     }\n1010: }\n1011: \n1012: func (e *executor) releaseExecutionSlot() {\n1013:     select {\n1014:     case <-e.executionSem:\n1015:     default:\n1016:     }\n1017: }\n1018: \n1019: func (e *executor) ExecuteAsync(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (ExecutionID, error) {\n1020:     if err := req.Validate(); err != nil {\n1021:         return \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrInvalidRequest, err)\n1022:     }\n1023: \n1024:     // Check queue capacity\n1025:     if e.queue.Size() >= e.config.MaxExecutionQueueSize {\n1026:         return \"\", ErrTooManyConcurrentExecutions\n1027:     }\n1028: \n1029:     // Enqueue\n1030:     id, err := e.queue.Enqueue(req)\n1031:     if err != nil {\n1032:         return \"\", err\n1033:     }\n1034: \n1035:     // Create initial status\n1036:     status := &ExecutionStatus{\n1037:         ID:    id,\n1038:         State: StatePending,\n1039:     }\n1040:     if err := e.store.CreateStatus(ctx, status); err != nil {\n1041:         e.queue.Remove(id)\n1042:         return \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create status: %w\", err)\n1043:     }\n1044: \n1045:     return id, nil\n1046: }\n1047: ```\n1048: \n1049: ### Error Wrapping and Propagation\n1050: \n1051: ```go\n1052: // Error wrapping pattern with context\n1053: if err != nil {\n1054:     return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to resolve sandbox for session %s: %w\", req.SessionID, err)\n1055: }\n1056: \n1057: // Error checking with context\n1058: if errors.Is(err, ErrSandboxUnavailable) {\n1059:     // Retry with backoff\n1060: }\n1061: \n1062: // Kubernetes API error mapping\n1063: func mapSandboxError(err error) error {\n1064:     if errors.Is(err, store.ErrNotFound) {\n1065:         return ErrSandboxUnavailable\n1066:     }\n1067:     return fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrSandboxUnavailable, err)\n1068: }\n1069: ```\n1070: \n1071: ---\n1072: \n1073: ## Testing Strategy\n1074: \n1075: ### Unit Tests\n1076: \n1077: ```go\n1078: func TestExecutor_Execute_Success(t *testing.T) {\n1079:     // Setup mocks\n1080:     mockStore := new(mockExecutionStore)\n1081:     mockResolver := new(mockSandboxResolver)\n1082:     mockRunner := new(mockSandboxRunner)\n1083: \n1084:     executor := NewExecutor(ExecutorConfig{\n1085:         DefaultTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n1086:     }, mockStore, mockResolver, mockRunner)\n1087: \n1088:     // Setup expectations\n1089:     sandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{\n1090:         SessionID: \"sess-123\",\n1091:         PodIP:     \"10.0.0.1\",\n1092:     }\n1093:     mockResolver.On(\"Resolve\", mock.Anything, \"sess-123\").Return(sandbox, nil)\n1094:     mockRunner.On(\"Run\", mock.Anything, sandbox, mock.Anything).Return(&ExecutionResult{\n1095:         ExitCode: 0,\n1096:         Stdout:   []byte(\"hello\\n\"),\n1097:     }, nil)\n1098: \n1099:     // Execute\n1100:     result, err := executor.Execute(context.Background(), ExecutionRequest{\n1101:         Command:   \"echo\",\n1102:         Args:      []string{\"hello\"},\n1103:         SessionID: \"sess-123\",\n1104:     })\n1105: \n1106:     // Assert\n1107:     assert.NoError(t, err)\n1108:     assert.Equal(t, 0, result.ExitCode)\n1109:     assert.Equal(t, \"hello\\n\", string(result.Stdout))\n1110:     mockResolver.AssertExpectations(t)\n1111:     mockRunner.AssertExpectations(t)\n1112: }\n1113: \n1114: func TestExecutor_Execute_InvalidCommand(t *testing.T) {\n1115:     executor := NewExecutor(DefaultConfig(), nil, nil, nil)\n1116: \n1117:     _, err := executor.Execute(context.Background(), ExecutionRequest{\n1118:         Command:   \"\",\n1119:         SessionID: \"sess-123\",\n1120:     })\n1121: \n1122:     assert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrInvalidCommand)\n1123: }\n1124: \n1125: func TestExecutor_Execute_Timeout(t *testing.T) {\n1126:     mockResolver := new(mockSandboxResolver)\n1127:     mockRunner := new(mockSandboxRunner)\n1128: \n1129:     executor := NewExecutor(ExecutorConfig{\n1130:         DefaultTimeout: 100 * time.Millisecond,\n1131:     }, nil, mockResolver, mockRunner)\n1132: \n1133:     sandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{SessionID: \"sess-123\"}\n1134:     mockResolver.On(\"Resolve\", mock.Anything, \"sess-123\").Return(sandbox, nil)\n1135:     mockRunner.On(\"Run\", mock.Anything, sandbox, mock.Anything).Run(func(args mock.Arguments) {\n1136:         ctx := args.Get(0).(context.Context)\n1137:         <-ctx.Done() // Block until cancelled\n1138:     }).Return(nil, context.DeadlineExceeded)\n1139: \n1140:     _, err := executor.Execute(context.Background(), ExecutionRequest{\n1141:         Command:   \"sleep\",\n1142:         Args:      []string{\"10\"},\n1143:         SessionID: \"sess-123\",\n1144:     })\n1145: \n1146:     assert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrTimeout)\n1147: }\n1148: \n1149: func TestExecutor_ExecuteAsync(t *testing.T) {\n1150:     mockStore := new(mockExecutionStore)\n1151:     mockQueue := new(mockExecutionQueue)\n1152: \n1153:     executor := &executor{\n1154:         store: mockStore,\n1155:         queue: mockQueue,\n1156:         config: ExecutorConfig{\n1157:             MaxExecutionQueueSize: 100,\n1158:         },\n1159:     }\n1160: \n1161:     mockQueue.On(\"Size\").Return(0)\n1162:     mockQueue.On(\"Enqueue\", mock.Anything).Return(ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\"), nil)\n1163:     mockStore.On(\"CreateStatus\", mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil)\n1164: \n1165:     id, err := executor.ExecuteAsync(context.Background(), ExecutionRequest{\n1166:         Command:   \"long-running-task\",\n1167:         SessionID: \"sess-123\",\n1168:     })\n1169: \n1170:     assert.NoError(t, err)\n1171:     assert.Equal(t, ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\"), id)\n1172:     mockQueue.AssertExpectations(t)\n1173:     mockStore.AssertExpectations(t)\n1174: }\n1175: \n1176: func TestExecutor_GetStatus(t *testing.T) {\n1177:     mockStore := new(mockExecutionStore)\n1178:     executor := &executor{store: mockStore}\n1179: \n1180:     expectedStatus := &ExecutionStatus{\n1181:         ID:    ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\"),\n1182:         State: StateRunning,\n1183:     }\n1184:     mockStore.On(\"GetStatus\", mock.Anything, ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\")).Return(expectedStatus, nil)\n1185: \n1186:     status, err := executor.GetStatus(context.Background(), ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\"))\n1187: \n1188:     assert.NoError(t, err)\n1189:     assert.Equal(t, StateRunning, status.State)\n1190: }\n1191: \n1192: func TestExecutor_Cancel(t *testing.T) {\n1193:     mockStore := new(mockExecutionStore)\n1194:     mockRunner := new(mockSandboxRunner)\n1195:     mockResolver := new(mockSandboxResolver)\n1196: \n1197:     executor := &executor{\n1198:         store:           mockStore,\n1199:         sandboxRunner:   mockRunner,\n1200:         sandboxResolver: mockResolver,\n1201:     }\n1202: \n1203:     status := &ExecutionStatus{\n1204:         ID:    ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\"),\n1205:         State: StateRunning,\n1206:     }\n1207:     sandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{SessionID: \"sess-123\"}\n1208: \n1209:     mockStore.On(\"GetStatus\", mock.Anything, ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\")).Return(status, nil)\n1210:     mockResolver.On(\"Resolve\", mock.Anything, \"sess-123\").Return(sandbox, nil)\n1211:     mockRunner.On(\"Cancel\", mock.Anything, sandbox, ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\")).Return(nil)\n1212:     mockStore.On(\"UpdateStatusWithTransition\", mock.Anything, ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\"), StateRunning, StateCancelled, mock.Anything).Return(nil)\n1213: \n1214:     err := executor.Cancel(context.Background(), ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\"))\n1215: \n1216:     assert.NoError(t, err)\n1217: }\n1218: \n1219: func TestExecutor_StreamOutput(t *testing.T) {\n1220:     executor := &executor{\n1221:         outputBuffers: make(map[ExecutionID]*OutputBuffer),\n1222:     }\n1223: \n1224:     // Create buffer with some output\n1225:     buf := NewOutputBuffer(ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\"), 100)\n1226:     buf.Write([]byte(\"line1\\n\"), Stdout)\n1227:     buf.Write([]byte(\"line2\\n\"), Stdout)\n1228:     executor.outputBuffers[ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\")] = buf\n1229: \n1230:     ch, err := executor.StreamOutput(context.Background(), ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\"))\n1231: \n1232:     assert.NoError(t, err)\n1233: \n1234:     // Receive chunks\n1235:     var chunks []OutputChunk\n1236:     for chunk := range ch {\n1237:         chunks = append(chunks, chunk)\n1238:     }\n1239: \n1240:     assert.Len(t, chunks, 2)\n1241:     assert.Equal(t, \"line1\\n\", string(chunks[0].Data))\n1242:     assert.Equal(t, \"line2\\n\", string(chunks[1].Data))\n1243: }\n1244: ```\n1245: \n1246: ### Integration Tests\n1247: \n1248: ```go\n1249: func TestIntegration_ExecuteWithRealStore(t *testing.T) {\n1250:     if testing.Short() {\n1251:         t.Skip(\"Skipping integration test\")\n1252:     }\n1253: \n1254:     // Setup real Redis store\n1255:     store := setupTestRedis(t)\n1256:     defer store.Close()\n1257: \n1258:     executor := NewExecutor(DefaultConfig(), store, mockResolver, mockRunner)\n1259: \n1260:     // Test full execution flow\n1261:     result, err := executor.Execute(context.Background(), ExecutionRequest{\n1262:         Command:   \"echo\",\n1263:         Args:      []string{\"integration test\"},\n1264:         SessionID: \"test-session\",\n1265:     })\n1266: \n1267:     assert.NoError(t, err)\n1268:     assert.Equal(t, 0, result.ExitCode)\n1269: }\n1270: ```\n1271: \n1272: ### Test Scenarios\n1273: \n1274: | Scenario | Test Case | Expected Result |\n1275: |----------|-----------|-----------------|\n1276: | Sync execution success | `TestExecute_Success` | Returns result with exit code 0 |\n1277: | Sync execution failure | `TestExecute_CommandFailure` | Returns result with non-zero exit code |\n1278: | Sync execution timeout | `TestExecute_Timeout` | Returns ErrTimeout |\n1279: | Invalid command | `TestExecute_InvalidCommand` | Returns ErrInvalidCommand |\n1280: | Invalid session | `TestExecute_InvalidSession` | Returns ErrInvalidSessionID |\n1281: | Async execution | `TestExecuteAsync` | Returns execution ID |\n1282: | Queue full | `TestExecuteAsync_QueueFull` | Returns ErrTooManyConcurrent |\n1283: | Get status | `TestGetStatus` | Returns correct status |\n1284: | Status not found | `TestGetStatus_NotFound` | Returns ErrExecutionNotFound |\n1285: | Cancel running | `TestCancel` | Updates status to cancelled |\n1286: | Cancel completed | `TestCancel_AlreadyComplete` | Returns ErrExecutionAlreadyComplete |\n1287: | Stream output | `TestStreamOutput` | Receives all output chunks |\n1288: | Context cancellation | `TestExecute_ContextCancel` | Returns ErrCancelled |\n1289: | Resource limits | `TestExecute_ResourceLimits` | Enforces constraints |\n1290: \n1291: ---\n1292: \n1293: ## Dependencies\n1294: \n1295: ### External Dependencies\n1296: \n1297: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n1298: |---------|---------|---------|\n1299: | `github.com/google/uuid` | v1.6.0 | ExecutionID generation |\n1300: | `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.32.0 | Kubernetes API client |\n1301: \n1302: ### Internal Dependencies\n1303: \n1304: | Package | Purpose |\n1305: |---------|---------|\n1306: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo shared types |\n1307: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Execution store interface |\n1308: \n1309: ### Downstream Consumers\n1310: \n1311: | Consumer | Usage |\n1312: |----------|-------|\n1313: | WorkloadManager | Execute commands in sandboxes |\n1314: | Session Manager | User session command execution |\n1315: | CLI Toolkit | Synchronous command execution |\n1316: | Idle Cleanup Worker | Query active executions |\n1317: \n1318: ---\n1319: \n1320: ## Performance Characteristics\n1321: \n1322: | Operation | Complexity | Latency | Notes |\n1323: |-----------|------------|---------|-------|\n1324: | Execute (sync) | O(1) | Command-dependent | Blocking until completion |\n1325: | ExecuteAsync | O(1) | < 10ms | Queue insertion |\n1326: | GetStatus | O(1) | < 5ms | Store lookup |\n1327: | Cancel | O(1) | < 10ms | Signal + status update |\n1328: | StreamOutput | O(n) | Real-time | n = output chunks |\n1329: | Resolve Sandbox | O(1) | < 5ms | Store or cache lookup |\n1330: \n1331: ### Resource Limits\n1332: \n1333: | Resource | Default | Maximum | Configurable |\n1334: |----------|---------|---------|--------------|\n1335: | Concurrent executions | 100 | 1000 | Yes |\n1336: | Execution queue size | 1000 | 10000 | Yes |\n1337: | Max output size | 10MB | 100MB | Yes |\n1338: | Output buffer size | 4KB | 1MB | Yes |\n1339: | Execution TTL | 24h | 7d | Yes |\n1340: \n1341: ---\n1342: \n1343: ## Security Considerations\n1344: \n1345: - **Command Validation**: Rejects commands with path traversal attempts (`..`, `//`)\n1346: - **Working Directory Restrictions**: Validates working directories against allowed paths\n1347: - **Environment Variable Filtering**: Validates env var names (alphanumeric + underscore)\n1348: - **Resource Limits**: Enforces CPU, memory, IO, and file descriptor limits\n1349: - **Sandbox Isolation**: All commands run in isolated sandbox environments\n1350: - **No Shell Access**: Direct command execution without shell interpolation\n1351: - **Output Size Limits**: Prevents memory exhaustion from large outputs\n1352: \n1353: ---\n1354: \n1355: ## References\n1356: \n1357: - [PicoD Proposal](proposal.md) — Feature proposal and requirements\n1358: - [PicoD Delta Spec](changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md) — API specification changes\n1359: - [PicoD Tests](changes/AR-015/tests.md) — Test specifications\n1360: - [client-go Library](deployment/client-go.md) — Kubernetes client patterns\n1361: - [AR-009 Sandbox](sandbox-orchestration/design.md) — Sandbox orchestration system\n1362: - [AR-012 Session Store](session-store/design.md) — Storage interface\n1363: - [AR-006 Lifecycle](changes/AR-006/design.md) — Lifecycle management patterns\n1364: \n1365: ---\n1366: \n1367: *AR-015 — Module: pkg/picod — Language: Go — Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 1367 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015 Design: PicoD Command Execution API\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-015  \n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M (Medium)\n\nThe PicoD Command Execution API provides a unified interface for executing commands within sandboxed environments in the agentcube platform. It supports both synchronous and asynchronous execution modes, resource constraint enforcement, output capture and streaming, and complete execution lifecycle management.\n\nThis implementation integrates with:\n- **Sandbox Interface (AR-009)**: For actual command execution in sandbox environments\n- **Status Store (AR-012/AR-013/AR-014)**: For execution status persistence\n- **client-go Library**: For Kubernetes API interactions with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775875300349,"end":1775875300372}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875300379,"sessionID":"ses_28595af03ffeB1qczelYixQTBJ","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6a8bab0014N3LXmyUV4FXUU","messageID":"msg_d7a6a793a001Dgbsfk6glSTl7n","sessionID":"ses_28595af03ffeB1qczelYixQTBJ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: PicoD File Management API\n2: \n3: ## AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n4: \n5: | Field | Value |\n6: |-------|-------|\n7: | **Module** | `pkg/picod` |\n8: | **Language** | Go |\n9: | **Size** | M (Medium) |\n10: | **Status** | Proposed |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Purpose\n15: \n16: Implement the PicoD file management API that provides a unified interface for file operations within sandboxed environments. This proposal delivers:\n17: \n18: 1. **File Upload/Download**: Transfer files between the host and sandbox environments with support for streaming large files\n19: 2. **Directory Listing**: Browse and query files within sandbox workspaces with filtering and pagination\n20: 3. **File Operations**: Create, delete, move, copy, and modify files and directories\n21: 4. **Path Security**: Enforce workspace boundaries and prevent path traversal attacks\n22: 5. **Quota Management**: Track and enforce storage limits per session\n23: \n24: This API serves as the file system interface between the agentcube platform and the sandbox orchestration system, enabling secure, quota-managed file operations with full audit logging.\n25: \n26: ---\n27: \n28: ## Scope\n29: \n30: ### In Scope\n31: \n32: | Item | Detail |\n33: |------|--------|\n34: | **FileManager Interface** | Core file management interface with CRUD operations |\n35: | **Upload Operations** | Single file upload, multi-file upload, chunked upload for large files |\n36: | **Download Operations** | File download, directory archive download, streaming download |\n37: | **Directory Operations** | List, create, delete directories; recursive operations |\n38: | **File Metadata** | Size, permissions, modification time, MIME type detection |\n39: | **Path Validation** | Workspace-relative paths, path traversal prevention |\n40: | **Quota Tracking** | Storage usage monitoring and limit enforcement |\n41: | **File Watching** | Optional file system change notifications |\n42: | **Error Types** | Domain-specific errors for file operation failures |\n43: | **Integration Points** | Integration with status store for operation tracking |\n44: \n45: ### Out of Scope\n46: \n47: - Changes to the sandbox orchestration interface (AR-009)\n48: - Modifications to storage implementations (AR-012/AR-013/AR-014)\n49: - HTTP server implementation (separate PicoD daemon)\n50: - JWT authentication layer\n51: - Command execution APIs (AR-015)\n52: - Real-time collaborative editing\n53: - Version control integration (Git operations)\n54: - File content search/indexing\n55: - Encryption at rest (handled at storage layer)\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## Design\n60: \n61: ### File Structure\n62: \n63: | File | Role | Lines (est.) |\n64: |------|------|--------------|\n65: | `pkg/picod/file_manager.go` | FileManager implementation | ~300 |\n66: | `pkg/picod/file_types.go` | File operation type definitions | ~120 |\n67: | `pkg/picod/upload.go` | Upload handling and chunking | ~150 |\n68: | `pkg/picod/download.go` | Download handling and streaming | ~150 |\n69: | `pkg/picod/path.go` | Path validation and security | ~100 |\n70: | `pkg/picod/quota.go` | Quota management and tracking | ~80 |\n71: | `pkg/picod/file_errors.go` | File-specific error definitions | ~60 |\n72: | `pkg/picod/file_manager_test.go` | Unit tests | ~250 |\n73: \n74: ### Architecture\n75: \n76: ```\n77: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n78: │                    Client Application                    │\n79: └─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────┘\n80:                       │\n81:                       ▼\n82: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n83: │              PicoD FileManager API                       │\n84: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n85: │  Upload()   │  Download()    │  List()                │\n86: │  Delete()   │  Move()        │  Copy()                │\n87: │  Mkdir()    │  GetMetadata() │  Watch()               │\n88: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n89: │              Sandbox Interface (AR-009)                  │\n90: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n91: │              Status Store (AR-012/13/14)                 │\n92: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n93: ```\n94: \n95: ### Core Types\n96: \n97: #### FileManager Interface\n98: \n99: ```go\n100: type FileManager interface {\n101:     // Upload operations\n102:     Upload(ctx context.Context, req UploadRequest) (*UploadResult, error)\n103:     UploadChunk(ctx context.Context, req UploadChunkRequest) (*UploadChunkResult, error)\n104:     \n105:     // Download operations\n106:     Download(ctx context.Context, req DownloadRequest) (*DownloadResult, error)\n107:     StreamDownload(ctx context.Context, req DownloadRequest) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n108:     \n109:     // File operations\n110:     Delete(ctx context.Context, req DeleteRequest) error\n111:     Move(ctx context.Context, req MoveRequest) error\n112:     Copy(ctx context.Context, req CopyRequest) error\n113:     \n114:     // Directory operations\n115:     List(ctx context.Context, req ListRequest) (*ListResult, error)\n116:     Mkdir(ctx context.Context, req MkdirRequest) error\n117:     Rmdir(ctx context.Context, req RmdirRequest) error\n118:     \n119:     // Metadata operations\n120:     GetMetadata(ctx context.Context, req MetadataRequest) (*FileMetadata, error)\n121:     SetPermissions(ctx context.Context, req PermissionsRequest) error\n122:     \n123:     // Quota operations\n124:     GetQuota(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*QuotaInfo, error)\n125:     \n126:     // Watching\n127:     Watch(ctx context.Context, req WatchRequest) (FileWatcher, error)\n128: }\n129: ```\n130: \n131: #### UploadRequest / UploadResult\n132: \n133: ```go\n134: type UploadRequest struct {\n135:     SessionID       string\n136:     SourcePath      string      // Path on host\n137:     DestinationPath string      // Path in sandbox (relative to workspace)\n138:     Overwrite       bool\n139:     ContentType     string\n140:     \n141:     // For chunked uploads\n142:     ChunkSize       int64       // 0 for auto-detect\n143:     TotalSize       int64       // Known size, 0 if unknown\n144: }\n145: \n146: type UploadResult struct {\n147:     FileID          string\n148:     Path            string\n149:     Size            int64\n150:     Checksum        string      // SHA-256\n151:     UploadedAt      time.Time\n152: }\n153: \n154: type UploadChunkRequest struct {\n155:     UploadID        string\n156:     ChunkIndex      int\n157:     ChunkData       io.Reader\n158:     ChunkSize       int64\n159:     IsLast          bool\n160: }\n161: \n162: type UploadChunkResult struct {\n163:     ChunkIndex      int\n164:     ReceivedBytes   int64\n165:     UploadComplete  bool\n166: }\n167: ```\n168: \n169: #### DownloadRequest / DownloadResult\n170: \n171: ```go\n172: type DownloadRequest struct {\n173:     SessionID       string\n174:     Path            string      // Path in sandbox (relative to workspace)\n175:     Recursive       bool        // For directories\n176:     ArchiveFormat   string      // \"zip\", \"tar\", \"tar.gz\" for recursive download\n177: }\n178: \n179: type DownloadResult struct {\n180:     FileID          string\n181:     Path            string\n182:     Size            int64\n183:     ContentType     string\n184:     Data            io.ReadCloser\n185:     Checksum        string      // SHA-256\n186: }\n187: ```\n188: \n189: #### ListRequest / ListResult\n190: \n191: ```go\n192: type ListRequest struct {\n193:     SessionID       string\n194:     Path            string\n195:     Recursive       bool\n196:     Pattern         string      // Glob pattern for filtering\n197:     IncludeHidden   bool\n198:     Pagination      *Pagination\n199: }\n200: \n201: type Pagination struct {\n202:     Limit   int\n203:     Offset  int\n204:     Cursor  string\n205: }\n206: \n207: type ListResult struct {\n208:     Entries         []FileInfo\n209:     TotalCount      int\n210:     NextCursor      string\n211: }\n212: \n213: type FileInfo struct {\n214:     Name            string\n215:     Path            string\n216:     Type            FileType      // file, directory, symlink\n217:     Size            int64\n218:     Permissions     os.FileMode\n219:     CreatedAt       time.Time\n220:     ModifiedAt      time.Time\n221:     Checksum        string        // For files\n222:     MimeType        string\n223: }\n224: \n225: type FileType string\n226: \n227: const (\n228:     FileTypeFile      FileType = \"file\"\n229:     FileTypeDirectory FileType = \"directory\"\n230:     FileTypeSymlink   FileType = \"symlink\"\n231: )\n232: ```\n233: \n234: #### DeleteRequest / MoveRequest / CopyRequest\n235: \n236: ```go\n237: type DeleteRequest struct {\n238:     SessionID       string\n239:     Path            string\n240:     Recursive       bool        // For directories\n241: }\n242: \n243: type MoveRequest struct {\n244:     SessionID       string\n245:     SourcePath      string\n246:     DestinationPath string\n247:     Overwrite       bool\n248: }\n249: \n250: type CopyRequest struct {\n251:     SessionID       string\n252:     SourcePath      string\n253:     DestinationPath string\n254:     Overwrite       bool\n255: }\n256: ```\n257: \n258: #### QuotaInfo\n259: \n260: ```go\n261: type QuotaInfo struct {\n262:     SessionID       string\n263:     UsedBytes       int64\n264:     TotalBytes      int64           // 0 for unlimited\n265:     AvailableBytes  int64\n266:     FileCount       int64\n267:     MaxFileCount    int64           // 0 for unlimited\n268: }\n269: ```\n270: \n271: ---\n272: \n273: ## Execution Flows\n274: \n275: ### File Upload (Small Files)\n276: \n277: ```\n278: Upload(ctx, req)\n279:     │\n280:     ▼\n281: Validate request parameters\n282:     │\n283:     ▼\n284: Resolve and validate destination path\n285:     │\n286:     ▼\n287: Check quota availability\n288:     │\n289:     ├─ Insufficient → Return ErrQuotaExceeded\n290:     │\n291:     ▼\n292: Upload file to sandbox\n293:     │\n294:     ▼\n295: Verify checksum\n296:     │\n297:     ▼\n298: Update quota tracking\n299:     │\n300:     ▼\n301: Return UploadResult\n302: ```\n303: \n304: ### File Upload (Large Files - Chunked)\n305: \n306: ```\n307: Upload(ctx, req) - Initialize\n308:     │\n309:     ▼\n310: Validate request parameters\n311:     │\n312:     ▼\n313: Create upload session\n314:     │\n315:     ▼\n316: Return UploadID\n317: \n318: UploadChunk(ctx, chunkReq) - Repeat for each chunk\n319:     │\n320:     ▼\n321: Validate upload session\n322:     │\n323:     ▼\n324: Receive chunk data\n325:     │\n326:     ▼\n327: Store chunk temporarily\n328:     │\n329:     ▼\n330: Update upload progress\n331:     │\n332:     ▼\n333: If IsLast:\n334:     │\n335:     ▼\n336: Assemble chunks\n337:     │\n338:     ▼\n339: Verify checksum\n340:     │\n341:     ▼\n342: Move to final destination\n343:     │\n344:     ▼\n345: Update quota tracking\n346:     │\n347:     ▼\n348: Return UploadChunkResult\n349: ```\n350: \n351: ### File Download\n352: \n353: ```\n354: Download(ctx, req)\n355:     │\n356:     ▼\n357: Validate request parameters\n358:     │\n359:     ▼\n360: Resolve and validate source path\n361:     │\n362:     ├─ Not found → Return ErrFileNotFound\n363:     │\n364:     ▼\n365: Check if path is directory and recursive flag\n366:     │\n367:     ├─ Directory + !Recursive → Return ErrIsDirectory\n368:     ├─ Directory + Recursive → Create archive stream\n369:     └─ File → Create file stream\n370:     │\n371:     ▼\n372: Stream data to client\n373:     │\n374:     ▼\n375: Return DownloadResult with ReadCloser\n376: ```\n377: \n378: ### Directory Listing\n379: \n380: ```\n381: List(ctx, req)\n382:     │\n383:     ▼\n384: Validate request parameters\n385:     │\n386:     ▼\n387: Resolve and validate path\n388:     │\n389:     ├─ Not found → Return ErrFileNotFound\n390:     │\n391:     ▼\n392: Query directory contents\n393:     │\n394:     ├─ !Recursive → List immediate children\n395:     └─ Recursive → Walk directory tree\n396:     │\n397:     ▼\n398: Apply pattern filter if specified\n399:     │\n400:     ▼\n401: Apply pagination\n402:     │\n403:     ▼\n404: Return ListResult\n405: ```\n406: \n407: ### File Deletion\n408: \n409: ```\n410: Delete(ctx, req)\n411:     │\n412:     ▼\n413: Validate request parameters\n414:     │\n415:     ▼\n416: Resolve and validate path\n417:     │\n418:     ├─ Not found → Return ErrFileNotFound\n419:     │\n420:     ▼\n421: Check if directory and recursive flag\n422:     │\n423:     ├─ Directory + !Recursive → Return ErrDirectoryNotEmpty\n424:     │\n425:     ▼\n426: Delete file/directory\n427:     │\n428:     ▼\n429: Update quota tracking\n430:     │\n431:     ▼\n432: Return nil\n433: ```\n434: \n435: ---\n436: \n437: ## Error Handling\n438: \n439: ### Error Types\n440: \n441: | Error | Code | Description |\n442: |-------|------|-------------|\n443: | `ErrInvalidRequest` | `INVALID_REQUEST` | Malformed file operation request |\n444: | `ErrFileNotFound` | `FILE_NOT_FOUND` | Specified path does not exist |\n445: | `ErrPathNotAllowed` | `PATH_NOT_ALLOWED` | Path outside workspace boundaries |\n446: | `ErrPathTraversal` | `PATH_TRAVERSAL` | Detected path traversal attempt |\n447: | `ErrPermissionDenied` | `PERMISSION_DENIED` | Insufficient permissions for operation |\n448: | `ErrQuotaExceeded` | `QUOTA_EXCEEDED` | Storage quota limit reached |\n449: | `ErrFileExists` | `FILE_EXISTS` | File already exists (without overwrite) |\n450: | `ErrIsDirectory` | `IS_DIRECTORY` | Expected file but got directory |\n451: | `ErrNotDirectory` | `NOT_DIRECTORY` | Expected directory but got file |\n452: | `ErrDirectoryNotEmpty` | `DIRECTORY_NOT_EMPTY` | Cannot delete non-empty directory |\n453: | `ErrTransferFailed` | `TRANSFER_FAILED` | Upload/download operation failed |\n454: | `ErrChecksumMismatch` | `CHECKSUM_MISMATCH` | Data integrity check failed |\n455: | `ErrSandboxUnavailable` | `SANDBOX_UNAVAILABLE` | Sandbox environment not available |\n456: \n457: ### FileError Structure\n458: \n459: ```go\n460: type FileError struct {\n461:     Code       string\n462:     Message    string\n463:     Path       string\n464:     Details    map[string]interface{}\n465: }\n466: \n467: func (e *FileError) Error() string {\n468:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s (path=%s)\", e.Code, e.Message, e.Path)\n469: }\n470: ```\n471: \n472: ---\n473: \n474: ## Path Security\n475: \n476: ### Path Validation Rules\n477: \n478: ```go\n479: type PathValidator struct {\n480:     WorkspaceRoot string\n481: }\n482: \n483: func (v *PathValidator) Validate(path string) (string, error) {\n484:     // 1. Clean the path\n485:     cleaned := filepath.Clean(path)\n486:     \n487:     // 2. Check for absolute paths\n488:     if filepath.IsAbs(cleaned) {\n489:         return \"\", ErrPathNotAllowed\n490:     }\n491:     \n492:     // 3. Resolve symlinks and check boundaries\n493:     fullPath := filepath.Join(v.WorkspaceRoot, cleaned)\n494:     resolved, err := filepath.EvalSymlinks(fullPath)\n495:     if err != nil {\n496:         return \"\", err\n497:     }\n498:     \n499:     // 4. Ensure resolved path is within workspace\n500:     if !strings.HasPrefix(resolved, v.WorkspaceRoot) {\n501:         return \"\", ErrPathTraversal\n502:     }\n503:     \n504:     // 5. Check for traversal patterns in original path\n505:     if strings.Contains(path, \"..\") {\n506:         return \"\", ErrPathTraversal\n507:     }\n508:     \n509:     return resolved, nil\n510: }\n511: ```\n512: \n513: ### Security Measures\n514: \n515: 1. **Workspace Isolation**: All paths are resolved relative to a sandbox-specific workspace root\n516: 2. **Symlink Resolution**: Symlinks are resolved and validated before operations\n517: 3. **Path Traversal Detection**: `../` patterns and absolute paths are rejected\n518: 4. **Permission Checks**: File permissions are validated before read/write operations\n519: 5. **Quota Enforcement**: Storage limits are checked before write operations\n520: \n521: ---\n522: \n523: ## Impact Analysis\n524: \n525: ### Files Created\n526: \n527: | File | Lines (est.) | Description |\n528: |------|--------------|-------------|\n529: | `pkg/picod/file_manager.go` | ~300 | Core FileManager implementation |\n530: | `pkg/picod/file_types.go` | ~120 | Type definitions for file operations |\n531: | `pkg/picod/upload.go` | ~150 | Upload handling and chunking logic |\n532: | `pkg/picod/download.go` | ~150 | Download handling and streaming |\n533: | `pkg/picod/path.go` | ~100 | Path validation and security |\n534: | `pkg/picod/quota.go` | ~80 | Quota management and tracking |\n535: | `pkg/picod/file_errors.go` | ~60 | File-specific error definitions |\n536: | `pkg/picod/file_manager_test.go` | ~250 | Unit tests |\n537: \n538: ### Dependencies\n539: \n540: ```go\n541: import (\n542:     \"context\"\n543:     \"crypto/sha256\"\n544:     \"errors\"\n545:     \"fmt\"\n546:     \"io\"\n547:     \"os\"\n548:     \"path/filepath\"\n549:     \"strings\"\n550:     \"time\"\n551:     \n552:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/sandbox\"\n553:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\"\n554: )\n555: ```\n556: \n557: | Package | Purpose |\n558: |---------|---------|\n559: | `pkg/sandbox` | Sandbox interface for file operations (AR-009) |\n560: | `pkg/store` | Status persistence for operation tracking (AR-012/13/14) |\n561: \n562: ### Downstream Consumers\n563: \n564: | Consumer | Usage |\n565: |----------|-------|\n566: | Session Manager | File operations within user sessions |\n567: | CLI Tooling | `kubectl-agentcube cp` commands |\n568: | HTTP API Layer | REST endpoints for file management |\n569: | IDE Integration | File sync for remote development |\n570: \n571: ### Performance Characteristics\n572: \n573: | Operation | Complexity | Notes |\n574: |-----------|------------|-------|\n575: | Upload (small) | O(n) | n = file size |\n576: | Upload (chunked) | O(n) | n = total file size |\n577: | Download | O(n) | n = file size |\n578: | List (non-recursive) | O(m) | m = directory entries |\n579: | List (recursive) | O(m) | m = total entries |\n580: | Delete | O(1) | Per file/directory |\n581: | Move/Copy | O(n) | n = file size |\n582: | Quota Check | O(1) | Cached value lookup |\n583: \n584: ---\n585: \n586: ## Alternatives Considered\n587: \n588: ### Alternative 1: Direct Sandbox File Access Without API Layer\n589: \n590: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n591: |--------|------------|\n592: | **Pros** | Simpler architecture; fewer abstraction layers; potentially better performance |\n593: | **Cons** | No centralized quota management; scattered permission checks; harder to implement unified audit logging; no support for chunked uploads |\n594: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — API layer provides necessary abstraction for quota management, security enforcement, and operation tracking |\n595: \n596: ### Alternative 2: Use Standard SFTP Protocol\n597: \n598: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n599: |--------|------------|\n600: | **Pros** | Industry standard; existing client libraries; familiar to users |\n601: | **Cons** | Additional protocol complexity; requires SFTP server in sandbox; harder to integrate with Kubernetes patterns; quota management requires custom extensions |\n602: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — Custom API better fits the agentcube architecture and provides more control over quota and security |\n603: \n604: ### Alternative 3: Leverage containerd/cri-o File Operations\n605: \n606: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n607: |--------|------------|\n608: | **Pros** | Native integration with container runtime; potentially more efficient |\n609: | **Cons** | Runtime-specific; limited to runtime capabilities; harder to implement features like chunked upload |\n610: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — Higher-level API provides better abstraction and portability across different sandbox implementations |\n611: \n612: ### Alternative 4: Event-Driven File Operations\n613: \n614: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n615: |--------|------------|\n616: | **Pros** | Better decoupling; natural fit for async operations; good for file watching |\n617: | **Cons** | Higher complexity; harder to implement synchronous operations like download; more moving parts |\n618: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — Direct method calls provide better control, simpler error handling, and are sufficient for the current use case |\n619: \n620: ---\n621: \n622: ## Risks and Mitigations\n623: \n624: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n625: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n626: | Path traversal vulnerabilities | Low | Critical | Strict path validation; workspace boundary enforcement; symlink resolution |\n627: | Quota bypass via sparse files | Low | Medium | Accurate size calculation; check both apparent and actual size |\n628: | Memory exhaustion from large uploads | Low | High | Streaming upload with chunked transfer; configurable chunk sizes |\n629: | Concurrent modification conflicts | Medium | Medium | Optimistic locking; ETag/checksum validation; atomic operations |\n630: | Storage exhaustion from failed uploads | Low | Medium | Automatic cleanup of incomplete uploads; upload session timeouts |\n631: | Denial of service via many small files | Medium | Medium | File count quotas; rate limiting on file creation |\n632: | Sandbox integration failures | Medium | High | Graceful error handling; fallback to error status; retry logic |\n633: \n634: ---\n635: \n636: ## Verification\n637: \n638: ### Unit Tests\n639: \n640: ```bash\n641: # Run all picod file manager tests\n642: make test PKG=./pkg/picod/...\n643: \n644: # Run with race detector\n645: go test -race ./pkg/picod/...\n646: \n647: # Run specific test categories\n648: go test -v ./pkg/picod/... -run \"TestUpload\"\n649: go test -v ./pkg/picod/... -run \"TestDownload\"\n650: go test -v ./pkg/picod/... -run \"TestPathValidation\"\n651: ```\n652: \n653: ### Integration Tests\n654: \n655: ```bash\n656: # Run integration tests (requires sandbox)\n657: go test -v ./pkg/picod/... -tags=integration\n658: \n659: # With coverage\n660: go test ./pkg/picod/... -coverprofile=coverage.out\n661: go tool cover -html=coverage.out\n662: ```\n663: \n664: ### Manual Verification\n665: \n666: ```bash\n667: # Build verification\n668: go build ./pkg/picod/...\n669: \n670: # Interface compliance check\n671: go build ./...\n672: \n673: # Lint check\n674: make lint PKG=./pkg/picod/...\n675: ```\n676: \n677: ### Test Scenarios\n678: \n679: | Scenario | Expected Result |\n680: |----------|-----------------|\n681: | Upload small file | Returns UploadResult with correct checksum |\n682: | Upload large file (chunked) | All chunks received, assembled correctly |\n683: | Upload to existing path (no overwrite) | Returns ErrFileExists |\n684: | Download file | Returns correct data with matching checksum |\n685: | Download directory (recursive) | Returns archive with all contents |\n686: | List directory | Returns all entries with correct metadata |\n687: | List with pattern filter | Returns only matching entries |\n688: | Delete file | File removed, quota updated |\n689: | Delete non-empty directory (no recursive) | Returns ErrDirectoryNotEmpty |\n690: | Path traversal attempt | Returns ErrPathTraversal |\n691: | Quota exceeded on upload | Returns ErrQuotaExceeded |\n692: | Invalid UTF-8 filename | Returns ErrInvalidRequest |\n693: | Concurrent uploads to same path | One succeeds, others fail with ErrFileExists |\n694: \n695: ---\n696: \n697: ## References\n698: \n699: - [PicoD Design](changes/AR-016/design.md) — Detailed design document\n700: - [PicoD Delta Spec](changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md) — API specification changes\n701: - [PicoD Tests](changes/AR-016/tests.md) — Test specifications\n702: - [AR-015 Command Execution](changes/AR-015/design.md) — Related command execution API\n703: - [AR-009 Sandbox](sandbox-orchestration/design.md) — Sandbox orchestration system\n704: - [AR-012 Session Store](session-store/design.md) — Storage interface\n705: - [client-go Library](deployment/client-go.md) — Kubernetes client patterns\n706: \n707: ---\n708: \n709: ## Success Criteria\n710: \n711: 1. ✅ FileManager interface fully implemented\n712: 2. ✅ Upload operations support both single-file and chunked modes\n713: 3. ✅ Download operations support streaming and archive creation\n714: 4. ✅ Directory listing with filtering and pagination\n715: 5. ✅ Complete file operations (delete, move, copy)\n716: 6. ✅ Path validation prevents traversal attacks\n717: 7. ✅ Quota tracking and enforcement\n718: 8. ✅ File watching support\n719: 9. ✅ Unit test coverage >= 85%\n720: 10. ✅ Integration tests passing\n721: 11. ✅ Race detector shows no issues\n722: \n723: ---\n724: \n725: *AR-016 — Module: pkg/picod — Language: Go — Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 725 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: PicoD File Management API\n\n## AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `pkg/picod` |\n| **Language** | Go |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the PicoD file management API that provides a unified interface for file operations within sandboxed environments. This proposal delivers:\n\n1. **File Upload/Download**: Transfer files between the host and sandbox environments with support for streaming large files\n2. **Directory Listing**: Browse and query files within sandbox workspaces with filtering and pagination\n3. **File Operations**: Create, delete, move, copy, and modify files and directories","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775875300345,"end":1775875300377}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875300383,"sessionID":"ses_28595af03ffeB1qczelYixQTBJ","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6a97c9001yybgxd7EM0Tbvl","messageID":"msg_d7a6a793a001Dgbsfk6glSTl7n","sessionID":"ses_28595af03ffeB1qczelYixQTBJ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/deployment/client-go.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/deployment/client-go.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # client-go library\n2: \n3: Generated Kubernetes client code for API group **`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` / `v1alpha1`**, module path **`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`**. Source reference: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`.\n4: \n5: ## Clientset\n6: \n7: ### `Interface` (`clientset/versioned/clientset.go`)\n8: \n9: ```go\n10: type Interface interface {\n11: \tDiscovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n12: \tRuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n13: }\n14: ```\n15: \n16: ### `Clientset` struct\n17: \n18: Embeds `*discovery.DiscoveryClient` and holds `runtimeV1alpha1 *runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Client`.\n19: \n20: **Constructors**\n21: \n22: - `NewForConfig(c *rest.Config) (*Clientset, error)`\n23: - `NewForConfigAndClient(c *rest.Config, httpClient *http.Client) (*Clientset, error)`\n24: - `NewForConfigOrDie(c *rest.Config) *Clientset`\n25: - `New(c rest.Interface) *Clientset`\n26: \n27: **Group accessor:** `RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## Typed client — `runtime/v1alpha1`\n32: \n33: ### `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` (`clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/runtime_client.go`)\n34: \n35: ```go\n36: type RuntimeV1alpha1Interface interface {\n37: \tRESTClient() rest.Interface\n38: \tAgentRuntimesGetter\n39: \tCodeInterpretersGetter\n40: }\n41: ```\n42: \n43: `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` implements this interface. REST defaults: `GroupVersion` = `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`.SchemeGroupVersion, `APIPath` = `/apis`, negotiated serializer from `clientset/versioned/scheme`.\n44: \n45: ### `AgentRuntimesGetter` / `AgentRuntimeInterface` (`.../agentruntime.go`)\n46: \n47: ```go\n48: type AgentRuntimesGetter interface {\n49: \tAgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeInterface\n50: }\n51: \n52: type AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n53: \tCreate(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n54: \tUpdate(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n55: \tUpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n56: \tDelete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n57: \tDeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n58: \tGet(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n59: \tList(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n60: \tWatch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n61: \tPatch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n62: \tAgentRuntimeExpansion\n63: }\n64: ```\n65: \n66: REST resource plural: **`agentruntimes`**.\n67: \n68: ### `CodeInterpretersGetter` / `CodeInterpreterInterface` (`.../codeinterpreter.go`)\n69: \n70: Same method shape as `AgentRuntimeInterface`, types `*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList`. REST resource plural: **`codeinterpreters`**.\n71: \n72: ### Expansion hooks (`generated_expansion.go`)\n73: