{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775875694147,"sessionID":"ses_28595af03ffeB1qczelYixQTBJ","part":{"id":"prt_d7a6ae5e8001bzIn30mljJT61N","messageID":"msg_d7a6ac996001g3pm8vv6l260Yy","sessionID":"ses_28595af03ffeB1qczelYixQTBJ","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","content":"# AR-016 Design: PicoD File Management API\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-016  \n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M (Medium)\n\nThe PicoD File Management API provides a unified interface for file operations within sandboxed environments. It supports file upload/download, directory listing, file operations (create, delete, move, copy), path security enforcement, and quota management.\n\nThis implementation integrates with:\n- **Sandbox Interface (AR-009)**: For actual file operations in sandbox environments\n- **Status Store (AR-012/AR-013/AR-014)**: For operation tracking and quota persistence\n- **PicoD Command Execution (AR-015)**: For complementary command-based file operations\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         Client Applications                                  │\n│  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐                         │\n│  │  Workload   │  │   CLI       │  │  Session    │                         │\n│  │  Manager    │  │   Toolkit   │  │  Manager    │                         │\n│  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘                         │\n└─────────┼────────────────┼────────────────┼────────────────────────────────┘\n          │                │                │\n          ▼                ▼                ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      PicoD FileManager API                                   │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│  │                      FileManager Interface                              │ │\n│  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────────┐ │ │\n│  │  │   Upload()      │  │   Download()    │  │   List()               │ │ │\n│  │  │   · Single      │  │   · Stream      │  │   · Filter             │ │ │\n│  │  │   · Chunked     │  │   · Archive     │  │   · Paginate           │ │ │\n│  │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └────────────────────────┘ │ │\n│  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────────┐ │ │\n│  │  │   Delete()      │  │   Move()        │  │   Copy()               │ │ │\n│  │  │   Mkdir()       │  │   Rmdir()       │  │   GetMetadata()        │ │ │\n│  │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └────────────────────────┘ │ │\n│  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                      File Operations Layer                                   │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  PathValidator   │  │  UploadManager   │  │  DownloadManager         │  │\n│  │  · Security      │  │  · Chunking      │  │  · Streaming             │  │\n│  │  · Normalization │  │  · Checksums     │  │  · Archiving             │  │\n│  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘  │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  QuotaManager    │  │  FileWatcher     │  │  TransferBuffer          │  │\n│  │  · Tracking      │  │  · Events        │  │  · Circular              │  │\n│  │  · Enforcement   │  │  · Notifications │  │  · Streaming             │  │\n│  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘  │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                      Sandbox Interface (AR-009)                              │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  Sandbox Resolver│  │  File Operations │  │  Workspace Access        │  │\n│  │  · Session lookup│  │  · Read/Write    │  │  · Isolation             │  │\n│  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘  │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                      Status Store (AR-012/13/14)                             │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐                                │\n│  │  Redis/Valkey    │  │  QuotaStore      │                                │\n│  │  · Upload state  │  │  · Usage cache   │                                │\n│  │  · TTL support   │  │  · Limits        │                                │\n│  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘                                │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                           File Upload Flow                                   │\n│                                                                              │\n│  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n│  │  Client  │──▶│  Upload  │──▶│ Validate │──▶│   Check  │──▶│  Resolve │  │\n│  │  Request │   │  Method  │   │  Request │   │   Quota  │   │   Path   │  │\n│  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └────┬─────┘   └────┬─────┘  │\n│                                                    │                │        │\n│                         ┌──────────────────────────┘                │        │\n│                         ▼                                           │        │\n│  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────┴─────┐  │\n│  │  Return  │◀──│  Update  │◀──│  Verify  │◀──│ Transfer │◀──│   Check    │  │\n│  │  Result  │   │  Quota   │   │ Checksum │   │   File   │   │  Sandbox   │  │\n│  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └────────────┘  │\n│                                                                              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Interactions\n\n| Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n|-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n| **FileManager** | Primary API for file operations | `UploadRequest`, `DownloadRequest`, `ListRequest`, etc. | `UploadResult`, `DownloadResult`, `ListResult`, error |\n| **PathValidator** | Validates and secures file paths | Raw path string | Validated, absolute path or error |\n| **UploadManager** | Handles upload operations with chunking | `UploadRequest`, `UploadChunkRequest` | `UploadResult`, `UploadChunkResult` |\n| **DownloadManager** | Handles download with streaming | `DownloadRequest` | `DownloadResult` with `io.ReadCloser` |\n| **QuotaManager** | Tracks and enforces storage quotas | Session ID, operation type, size | Quota status, allowance or error |\n| **FileWatcher** | Provides file change notifications | `WatchRequest` | File event channel |\n| **SandboxResolver** | Resolves session IDs to sandbox | `SessionID` | `SandboxInfo` |\n| **TransferBuffer** | Buffers transfer data | Data chunks | Buffered data for streaming |\n\n---\n\n## Directory Structure\n\n```\npkg/picod/\n├── file_manager.go          # FileManager interface and implementation (~300 lines)\n├── file_types.go            # File operation type definitions (~120 lines)\n├── upload.go                # Upload handling and chunking (~150 lines)\n├── download.go              # Download handling and streaming (~150 lines)\n├── path.go                  # Path validation and security (~100 lines)\n├── quota.go                 # Quota management and tracking (~80 lines)\n├── file_errors.go           # File-specific error definitions (~60 lines)\n└── file_manager_test.go     # Unit tests (~250 lines)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Request DTOs\n\n#### UploadRequest / UploadResult\n\n```go\n// UploadRequest contains parameters for file upload.\ntype UploadRequest struct {\n\t// SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n\tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n\n\t// SourcePath is the path on the host (required)\n\tSourcePath string `json:\"sourcePath\" validate:\"required\"`\n\n\t// DestinationPath is the path in sandbox, relative to workspace (required)\n\tDestinationPath string `json:\"destinationPath\" validate:\"required\"`\n\n\t// Overwrite allows overwriting existing files\n\tOverwrite bool `json:\"overwrite,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// ContentType specifies the MIME type (auto-detected if empty)\n\tContentType string `json:\"contentType,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// ChunkSize for chunked uploads (0 for auto-detect)\n\tChunkSize int64 `json:\"chunkSize,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// TotalSize is the known total size (0 if unknown)\n\tTotalSize int64 `json:\"totalSize,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// UploadResult contains the result of a successful upload.\ntype UploadResult struct {\n\t// FileID is a unique identifier for the uploaded file\n\tFileID string `json:\"fileId\"`\n\n\t// Path is the final path in the sandbox\n\tPath string `json:\"path\"`\n\n\t// Size is the uploaded file size in bytes\n\tSize int64 `json:\"size\"`\n\n\t// Checksum is the SHA-256 hash of the file\n\tChecksum string `json:\"checksum\"`\n\n\t// UploadedAt is the timestamp of successful upload\n\tUploadedAt time.Time `json:\"uploadedAt\"`\n}\n\n// UploadChunkRequest represents a chunk in a chunked upload.\ntype UploadChunkRequest struct {\n\t// UploadID identifies the upload session\n\tUploadID string `json:\"uploadId\" validate:\"required\"`\n\n\t// ChunkIndex is the 0-based chunk index\n\tChunkIndex int `json:\"chunkIndex\" validate:\"gte=0\"`\n\n\t// ChunkData contains the chunk data\n\tChunkData io.Reader `json:\"-\"`\n\n\t// ChunkSize is the size of this chunk\n\tChunkSize int64 `json:\"chunkSize\" validate:\"gt=0\"`\n\n\t// IsLast indicates this is the final chunk\n\tIsLast bool `json:\"isLast\"`\n}\n\n// UploadChunkResult contains the result of a chunk upload.\ntype UploadChunkResult struct {\n\t// ChunkIndex confirms the received chunk index\n\tChunkIndex int `json:\"chunkIndex\"`\n\n\t// ReceivedBytes confirms bytes received\n\tReceivedBytes int64 `json:\"receivedBytes\"`\n\n\t// UploadComplete indicates if the upload is finished\n\tUploadComplete bool `json:\"uploadComplete\"`\n}\n\n// Validate validates the upload request.\nfunc (r *UploadRequest) Validate() error {\n\tif strings.TrimSpace(r.SessionID) == \"\" {\n\t\treturn ErrInvalidSessionID\n\t}\n\tif strings.TrimSpace(r.SourcePath) == \"\" {\n\t\treturn ErrInvalidSourcePath\n\t}\n\tif strings.TrimSpace(r.DestinationPath) == \"\" {\n\t\treturn ErrInvalidDestinationPath\n\t}\n\tif strings.Contains(r.DestinationPath, \"..\") {\n\t\treturn ErrPathTraversal\n\t}\n\tif filepath.IsAbs(r.DestinationPath) {\n\t\treturn ErrPathNotAllowed\n\t}\n\treturn nil\n}\n```\n\n#### DownloadRequest / DownloadResult\n\n```go\n// DownloadRequest contains parameters for file download.\ntype DownloadRequest struct {\n\t// SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n\tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n\n\t// Path is the file path in the sandbox (required)\n\tPath string `json:\"path\" validate:\"required\"`\n\n\t// Recursive enables downloading directories as archives\n\tRecursive bool `json:\"recursive,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// ArchiveFormat for recursive downloads: \"zip\", \"tar\", \"tar.gz\"\n\tArchiveFormat string `json:\"archiveFormat,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// DownloadResult contains the result of a successful download.\ntype DownloadResult struct {\n\t// FileID is a unique identifier for the file\n\tFileID string `json:\"fileId\"`\n\n\t// Path is the file path\n\tPath string `json:\"path\"`\n\n\t// Size is the file size in bytes\n\tSize int64 `json:\"size\"`\n\n\t// ContentType is the MIME type\n\tContentType string `json:\"contentType\"`\n\n\t// Data provides a ReadCloser for streaming the file\n\tData io.ReadCloser `json:\"-\"`\n\n\t// Checksum is the SHA-256 hash\n\tChecksum string `json:\"checksum\"`\n\n\t// IsArchive indicates if this is an archive stream\n\tIsArchive bool `json:\"isArchive,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// Validate validates the download request.\nfunc (r *DownloadRequest) Validate() error {\n\tif strings.TrimSpace(r.SessionID) == \"\" {\n\t\treturn ErrInvalidSessionID\n\t}\n\tif strings.TrimSpace(r.Path) == \"\" {\n\t\treturn ErrInvalidPath\n\t}\n\tif strings.Contains(r.Path, \"..\") {\n\t\treturn ErrPathTraversal\n\t}\n\tif r.Recursive && r.ArchiveFormat != \"\" {\n\t\tvalidFormats := []string{\"zip\", \"tar\", \"tar.gz\"}\n\t\tif !slices.Contains(validFormats, r.ArchiveFormat) {\n\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"%w: archive format must be zip, tar, or tar.gz\", ErrInvalidRequest)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn nil\n}\n```\n\n#### ListRequest / ListResult\n\n```go\n// ListRequest contains parameters for directory listing.\ntype ListRequest struct {\n\t// SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n\tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n\n\t// Path is the directory to list (empty for root)\n\tPath string `json:\"path,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// Recursive lists subdirectories\n\tRecursive bool `json:\"recursive,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// Pattern is a glob pattern for filtering (e.g., \"*.go\")\n\tPattern string `json:\"pattern,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// IncludeHidden includes dotfiles\n\tIncludeHidden bool `json:\"includeHidden,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// Pagination controls result pagination\n\tPagination *Pagination `json:\"pagination,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// Pagination controls list result pagination.\ntype Pagination struct {\n\t// Limit is the maximum number of results\n\tLimit int `json:\"limit\" validate:\"gt=0,lte=1000\"`\n\n\t// Offset is the number of results to skip\n\tOffset int `json:\"offset\" validate:\"gte=0\"`\n\n\t// Cursor is an opaque pagination token\n\tCursor string `json:\"cursor,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// ListResult contains the directory listing.\ntype ListResult struct {\n\t// Entries is the list of file/directory entries\n\tEntries []FileInfo `json:\"entries\"`\n\n\t// TotalCount is the total number of entries (for pagination)\n\tTotalCount int `json:\"totalCount\"`\n\n\t// NextCursor for fetching the next page\n\tNextCursor string `json:\"nextCursor,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// FileInfo represents metadata about a file or directory.\ntype FileInfo struct {\n\t// Name is the entry name\n\tName string `json:\"name\"`\n\n\t// Path is the relative path from workspace root\n\tPath string `json:\"path\"`\n\n\t// Type indicates file, directory, or symlink\n\tType FileType `json:\"type\"`\n\n\t// Size in bytes (files only)\n\tSize int64 `json:\"size,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// Permissions in Unix format\n\tPermissions os.FileMode `json:\"permissions\"`\n\n\t// CreatedAt timestamp\n\tCreatedAt time.Time `json:\"createdAt\"`\n\n\t// ModifiedAt timestamp\n\tModifiedAt time.Time `json:\"modifiedAt\"`\n\n\t// Checksum for files (SHA-256)\n\tChecksum string `json:\"checksum,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// MimeType for files\n\tMimeType string `json:\"mimeType,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// FileType indicates the type of filesystem entry.\ntype FileType string\n\nconst (\n\t// FileTypeFile is a regular file\n\tFileTypeFile FileType = \"file\"\n\n\t// FileTypeDirectory is a directory\n\tFileTypeDirectory FileType = \"directory\"\n\n\t// FileTypeSymlink is a symbolic link\n\tFileTypeSymlink FileType = \"symlink\"\n)\n```\n\n#### File Operation Requests\n\n```go\n// DeleteRequest contains parameters for file deletion.\ntype DeleteRequest struct {\n\t// SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n\tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n\n\t// Path is the file or directory to delete (required)\n\tPath string `json:\"path\" validate:\"required\"`\n\n\t// Recursive deletes directories and contents\n\tRecursive bool `json:\"recursive,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// MoveRequest contains parameters for moving/renaming files.\ntype MoveRequest struct {\n\t// SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n\tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n\n\t// SourcePath is the original path (required)\n\tSourcePath string `json:\"sourcePath\" validate:\"required\"`\n\n\t// DestinationPath is the new path (required)\n\tDestinationPath string `json:\"destinationPath\" validate:\"required\"`\n\n\t// Overwrite allows overwriting existing files\n\tOverwrite bool `json:\"overwrite,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// CopyRequest contains parameters for copying files.\ntype CopyRequest struct {\n\t// SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n\tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n\n\t// SourcePath is the source file path (required)\n\tSourcePath string `json:\"sourcePath\" validate:\"required\"`\n\n\t// DestinationPath is the destination path (required)\n\tDestinationPath string `json:\"destinationPath\" validate:\"required\"`\n\n\t// Overwrite allows overwriting existing files\n\tOverwrite bool `json:\"overwrite,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// MkdirRequest contains parameters for creating directories.\ntype MkdirRequest struct {\n\t// SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n\tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n\n\t// Path is the directory path to create (required)\n\tPath string `json:\"path\" validate:\"required\"`\n\n\t// Permissions for the new directory (default: 0755)\n\tPermissions os.FileMode `json:\"permissions,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// CreateParents creates parent directories if needed\n\tCreateParents bool `json:\"createParents,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// RmdirRequest contains parameters for removing directories.\ntype RmdirRequest struct {\n\t// SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n\tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n\n\t// Path is the directory to remove (required)\n\tPath string `json:\"path\" validate:\"required\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### MetadataRequest / FileMetadata\n\n```go\n// MetadataRequest contains parameters for retrieving file metadata.\ntype MetadataRequest struct {\n\t// SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n\tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n\n\t// Path is the file or directory path (required)\n\tPath string `json:\"path\" validate:\"required\"`\n}\n\n// FileMetadata contains comprehensive file metadata.\ntype FileMetadata struct {\n\t// FileInfo contains basic file information\n\tFileInfo FileInfo `json:\"fileInfo\"`\n\n\t// IsReadable indicates read permission\n\tIsReadable bool `json:\"isReadable\"`\n\n\t// IsWritable indicates write permission\n\tIsWritable bool `json:\"isWritable\"`\n\n\t// IsExecutable indicates execute permission\n\tIsExecutable bool `json:\"isExecutable\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Domain Types\n\n#### QuotaInfo / QuotaManager\n\n```go\n// QuotaInfo represents storage quota information for a session.\ntype QuotaInfo struct {\n\t// SessionID identifies the session\n\tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\"`\n\n\t// UsedBytes is the current storage usage\n\tUsedBytes int64 `json:\"usedBytes\"`\n\n\t// TotalBytes is the quota limit (0 for unlimited)\n\tTotalBytes int64 `json:\"totalBytes\"`\n\n\t// AvailableBytes is the remaining quota\n\tAvailableBytes int64 `json:\"availableBytes\"`\n\n\t// FileCount is the current number of files\n\tFileCount int64 `json:\"fileCount\"`\n\n\t// MaxFileCount is the file limit (0 for unlimited)\n\tMaxFileCount int64 `json:\"maxFileCount\"`\n}\n\n// QuotaManager defines the interface for quota management.\ntype QuotaManager interface {\n\t// GetQuota retrieves quota information for a session\n\tGetQuota(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*QuotaInfo, error)\n\n\t// CheckUpload checks if an upload of size bytes is allowed\n\tCheckUpload(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, size int64) error\n\n\t// UpdateQuota updates quota after a file operation\n\tUpdateQuota(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, deltaBytes, deltaFiles int64) error\n\n\t// SetQuota sets quota limits for a session\n\tSetQuota(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, totalBytes, maxFileCount int64) error\n}\n```\n\n#### PathValidator\n\n```go\n// PathValidator validates and sanitizes file paths.\ntype PathValidator struct {\n\t// WorkspaceRoot is the base directory for all operations\n\tWorkspaceRoot string\n}\n\n// ValidationResult contains the validated path and metadata.\ntype ValidationResult struct {\n\t// CleanedPath is the sanitized relative path\n\tCleanedPath string\n\n\t// AbsolutePath is the resolved absolute path\n\tAbsolutePath string\n\n\t// IsWithinWorkspace confirms path is inside workspace\n\tIsWithinWorkspace bool\n}\n\n// Validate validates a path and returns the resolved result.\nfunc (v *PathValidator) Validate(path string) (*ValidationResult, error) {\n\t// Clean the path\n\tcleaned := filepath.Clean(path)\n\n\t// Check for absolute paths\n\tif filepath.IsAbs(cleaned) {\n\t\treturn nil, ErrPathNotAllowed\n\t}\n\n\t// Check for traversal patterns\n\tif strings.Contains(cleaned, \"..\") || strings.HasPrefix(cleaned, \"..\") {\n\t\treturn nil, ErrPathTraversal\n\t}\n\n\t// Resolve to absolute path\n\tabsPath := filepath.Join(v.WorkspaceRoot, cleaned)\n\n\t// Verify the path is within workspace (resolves symlinks)\n\tresolved, err := filepath.EvalSymlinks(absPath)\n\tif err != nil && !os.IsNotExist(err) {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrPathNotAllowed, err)\n\t}\n\n\tif err == nil {\n\t\t// Path exists - check it's within workspace\n\t\tif !strings.HasPrefix(resolved, v.WorkspaceRoot) {\n\t\t\treturn nil, ErrPathTraversal\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Check parent directories exist and are within workspace\n\tdir := filepath.Dir(absPath)\n\tif dir != v.WorkspaceRoot {\n\t\tresolvedDir, err := filepath.EvalSymlinks(dir)\n\t\tif err != nil && !os.IsNotExist(err) {\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrPathNotAllowed, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\tif err == nil && !strings.HasPrefix(resolvedDir, v.WorkspaceRoot) {\n\t\t\treturn nil, ErrPathTraversal\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn &ValidationResult{\n\t\tCleanedPath:       cleaned,\n\t\tAbsolutePath:      absPath,\n\t\tIsWithinWorkspace: true,\n\t}, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### FileWatcher / WatchRequest\n\n```go\n// WatchRequest contains parameters for file watching.\ntype WatchRequest struct {\n\t// SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n\tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n\n\t// Path is the directory or file to watch\n\tPath string `json:\"path,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// Recursive watches subdirectories\n\tRecursive bool `json:\"recursive,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// Events filters event types (empty for all)\n\tEvents []FileEventType `json:\"events,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// FileEventType indicates the type of file event.\ntype FileEventType string\n\nconst (\n\t// FileEventCreate indicates a file was created\n\tFileEventCreate FileEventType = \"create\"\n\n\t// FileEventWrite indicates a file was modified\n\tFileEventWrite FileEventType = \"write\"\n\n\t// FileEventRemove indicates a file was removed\n\tFileEventRemove FileEventType = \"remove\"\n\n\t// FileEventRename indicates a file was renamed\n\tFileEventRename FileEventType = \"rename\"\n\n\t// FileEventChmod indicates permissions changed\n\tFileEventChmod FileEventType = \"chmod\"\n)\n\n// FileEvent represents a file system event.\ntype FileEvent struct {\n\t// Type is the event type\n\tType FileEventType `json:\"type\"`\n\n\t// Path is the affected file path\n\tPath string `json:\"path\"`\n\n\t// OldPath is the previous path for rename events\n\tOldPath string `json:\"oldPath,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// Timestamp is when the event occurred\n\tTimestamp time.Time `json:\"timestamp\"`\n}\n\n// FileWatcher provides file system change notifications.\ntype FileWatcher interface {\n\t// Events returns a channel for file events\n\tEvents() <-chan FileEvent\n\n\t// Errors returns a channel for watch errors\n\tErrors() <-chan error\n\n\t// Stop stops the watcher\n\tStop() error\n}\n```\n\n### Internal Types\n\n#### FileManager\n\n```go\n// FileManager defines the interface for file operations in sandboxes.\ntype FileManager interface {\n\t// Upload uploads a file to the sandbox\n\tUpload(ctx context.Context, req UploadRequest) (*UploadResult, error)\n\n\t// UploadChunk uploads a chunk in a chunked upload\n\tUploadChunk(ctx context.Context, req UploadChunkRequest) (*UploadChunkResult, error)\n\n\t// Download downloads a file from the sandbox\n\tDownload(ctx context.Context, req DownloadRequest) (*DownloadResult, error)\n\n\t// StreamDownload returns a ReadCloser for streaming download\n\tStreamDownload(ctx context.Context, req DownloadRequest) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n\n\t// List lists directory contents\n\tList(ctx context.Context, req ListRequest) (*ListResult, error)\n\n\t// Delete deletes a file or directory\n\tDelete(ctx context.Context, req DeleteRequest) error\n\n\t// Move moves/renames a file or directory\n\tMove(ctx context.Context, req MoveRequest) error\n\n\t// Copy copies a file or directory\n\tCopy(ctx context.Context, req CopyRequest) error\n\n\t// Mkdir creates a directory\n\tMkdir(ctx context.Context, req MkdirRequest) error\n\n\t// Rmdir removes a directory\n\tRmdir(ctx context.Context, req RmdirRequest) error\n\n\t// GetMetadata retrieves file metadata\n\tGetMetadata(ctx context.Context, req MetadataRequest) (*FileMetadata, error)\n\n\t// SetPermissions sets file permissions\n\tSetPermissions(ctx context.Context, sessionID, path string, mode os.FileMode) error\n\n\t// GetQuota retrieves quota information\n\tGetQuota(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*QuotaInfo, error)\n\n\t// Watch starts watching a path for changes\n\tWatch(ctx context.Context, req WatchRequest) (FileWatcher, error)\n}\n\n// fileManager implements FileManager.\ntype fileManager struct {\n\t// validator validates file paths\n\tvalidator *PathValidator\n\n\t// quotaManager manages storage quotas\n\tquotaManager QuotaManager\n\n\t// sandboxResolver resolves session IDs\n\tsandboxResolver SandboxResolver\n\n\t// uploadSessions tracks active chunked uploads\n\tuploadSessions map[string]*uploadSession\n\n\t// mu protects uploadSessions\n\tmu sync.RWMutex\n\n\t// config contains file manager configuration\n\tconfig FileManagerConfig\n}\n\n// uploadSession tracks state for chunked uploads.\ntype uploadSession struct {\n\tID            string\n\tSessionID     string\n\tDestination   string\n\tTotalSize     int64\n\tReceivedBytes int64\n\tChunkSize     int64\n\tChunks        map[int]bool\n\tTempDir       string\n\tCreatedAt     time.Time\n\tLastActivity  time.Time\n}\n```\n\n#### FileManagerConfig\n\n```go\n// FileManagerConfig contains configuration for FileManager.\ntype FileManagerConfig struct {\n\t// MaxUploadSize is the maximum allowed upload size (default: 1GB)\n\tMaxUploadSize int64\n\n\t// MaxChunkSize is the maximum chunk size for uploads (default: 64MB)\n\tMaxChunkSize int64\n\n\t// DefaultChunkSize is the default chunk size (default: 16MB)\n\tDefaultChunkSize int64\n\n\t// UploadSessionTimeout is how long to keep incomplete upload sessions (default: 1h)\n\tUploadSessionTimeout time.Duration\n\n\t// MaxConcurrentUploads limits concurrent uploads per session (default: 5)\n\tMaxConcurrentUploads int\n\n\t// MaxConcurrentDownloads limits concurrent downloads per session (default: 5)\n\tMaxConcurrentDownloads int\n\n\t// StreamBufferSize is the buffer size for streaming (default: 32KB)\n\tStreamBufferSize int\n\n\t// ArchiveCompressionLevel for zip/tar.gz archives (default: 6)\n\tArchiveCompressionLevel int\n}\n\n// DefaultFileManagerConfig returns default configuration.\nfunc DefaultFileManagerConfig() FileManagerConfig {\n\treturn FileManagerConfig{\n\t\tMaxUploadSize:           1024 * 1024 * 1024, // 1GB\n\t\tMaxChunkSize:            64 * 1024 * 1024,   // 64MB\n\t\tDefaultChunkSize:        16 * 1024 * 1024,   // 16MB\n\t\tUploadSessionTimeout:    time.Hour,\n\t\tMaxConcurrentUploads:    5,\n\t\tMaxConcurrentDownloads:  5,\n\t\tStreamBufferSize:        32 * 1024, // 32KB\n\t\tArchiveCompressionLevel: 6,\n\t}\n}\n\n// ConfigFromEnv loads configuration from environment variables.\nfunc ConfigFromEnv() FileManagerConfig {\n\tcfg := DefaultFileManagerConfig()\n\n\tif v := os.Getenv(\"PICOD_MAX_UPLOAD_SIZE\"); v != \"\" {\n\t\tif n, err := strconv.ParseInt(v, 10, 64); err == nil {\n\t\t\tcfg.MaxUploadSize = n\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tif v := os.Getenv(\"PICOD_MAX_CHUNK_SIZE\"); v != \"\" {\n\t\tif n, err := strconv.ParseInt(v, 10, 64); err == nil {\n\t\t\tcfg.MaxChunkSize = n\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tif v := os.Getenv(\"PICOD_UPLOAD_SESSION_TIMEOUT\"); v != \"\" {\n\t\tif d, err := time.ParseDuration(v); err == nil {\n\t\t\tcfg.UploadSessionTimeout = d\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn cfg\n}\n```\n\n### Constants\n\n```go\n// Default configuration values\nconst (\n\t// DefaultMaxUploadSize is 1GB\n\tDefaultMaxUploadSize = 1024 * 1024 * 1024\n\n\t// DefaultChunkSize is 16MB\n\tDefaultChunkSize = 16 * 1024 * 1024\n\n\t// DefaultStreamBufferSize is 32KB\n\tDefaultStreamBufferSize = 32 * 1024\n\n\t// UploadIDLength is the length of generated upload IDs\n\tUploadIDLength = 16\n\n\t// UploadIDPrefix is the prefix for upload IDs\n\tUploadIDPrefix = \"upload-\"\n\n\t// FileIDLength is the length of generated file IDs\n\tFileIDLength = 16\n\n\t// FileIDPrefix is the prefix for file IDs\n\tFileIDPrefix = \"file-\"\n)\n\n// Error codes\nconst (\n\t// ErrorCodeInvalidRequest indicates malformed request\n\tErrorCodeInvalidRequest = \"INVALID_REQUEST\"\n\n\t// ErrorCodeInvalidSessionID indicates missing or invalid session ID\n\tErrorCodeInvalidSessionID = \"INVALID_SESSION_ID\"\n\n\t// ErrorCodeInvalidPath indicates invalid path\n\tErrorCodeInvalidPath = \"INVALID_PATH\"\n\n\t// ErrorCodePathTraversal indicates path traversal attempt\n\tErrorCodePathTraversal = \"PATH_TRAVERSAL\"\n\n\t// ErrorCodePathNotAllowed indicates path outside workspace\n\tErrorCodePathNotAllowed = \"PATH_NOT_ALLOWED\"\n\n\t// ErrorCodeFileNotFound indicates file does not exist\n\tErrorCodeFileNotFound = \"FILE_NOT_FOUND\"\n\n\t// ErrorCodeFileExists indicates file already exists\n\tErrorCodeFileExists = \"FILE_EXISTS\"\n\n\t// ErrorCodeIsDirectory indicates expected file but got directory\n\tErrorCodeIsDirectory = \"IS_DIRECTORY\"\n\n\t// ErrorCodeNotDirectory indicates expected directory but got file\n\tErrorCodeNotDirectory = \"NOT_DIRECTORY\"\n\n\t// ErrorCodeDirectoryNotEmpty indicates non-empty directory deletion\n\tErrorCodeDirectoryNotEmpty = \"DIRECTORY_NOT_EMPTY\"\n\n\t// ErrorCodeQuotaExceeded indicates storage quota exceeded\n\tErrorCodeQuotaExceeded = \"QUOTA_EXCEEDED\"\n\n\t// ErrorCodePermissionDenied indicates insufficient permissions\n\tErrorCodePermissionDenied = \"PERMISSION_DENIED\"\n\n\t// ErrorCodeTransferFailed indicates upload/download failure\n\tErrorCodeTransferFailed = \"TRANSFER_FAILED\"\n\n\t// ErrorCodeChecksumMismatch indicates checksum verification failed\n\tErrorCodeChecksumMismatch = \"CHECKSUM_MISMATCH\"\n\n\t// ErrorCodeSandboxUnavailable indicates sandbox not accessible\n\tErrorCodeSandboxUnavailable = \"SANDBOX_UNAVAILABLE\"\n\n\t// ErrorCodeUploadSessionNotFound indicates upload session expired/invalid\n\tErrorCodeUploadSessionNotFound = \"UPLOAD_SESSION_NOT_FOUND\"\n\n\t// ErrorCodeUploadSessionExpired indicates upload session timeout\n\tErrorCodeUploadSessionExpired = \"UPLOAD_SESSION_EXPIRED\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### FileManager Interface\n\n```go\n// FileManager is the primary API for PicoD file operations.\ntype FileManager interface {\n\t// Upload uploads a file to the sandbox.\n\t//\n\t// Parameters:\n\t//   - ctx: Context for cancellation and timeouts\n\t//   - req: Upload request containing source, destination, and options\n\t//\n\t// Returns:\n\t//   - *UploadResult: Result containing file ID, size, and checksum\n\t//   - error: ErrInvalidRequest, ErrPathTraversal, ErrQuotaExceeded, etc.\n\tUpload(ctx context.Context, req UploadRequest) (*UploadResult, error)\n\n\t// UploadChunk uploads a chunk in a chunked upload session.\n\t//\n\t// Parameters:\n\t//   - ctx: Context for the operation\n\t//   - req: Chunk upload request with upload ID and chunk data\n\t//\n\t// Returns:\n\t//   - *UploadChunkResult: Result containing completion status\n\t//   - error: ErrUploadSessionNotFound, ErrChecksumMismatch, etc.\n\tUploadChunk(ctx context.Context, req UploadChunkRequest) (*UploadChunkResult, error)\n\n\t// Download downloads a file from the sandbox.\n\t//\n\t// Parameters:\n\t//   - ctx: Context for cancellation and timeouts\n\t//   - req: Download request containing path and options\n\t//\n\t// Returns:\n\t//   - *DownloadResult: Result with file metadata and io.ReadCloser\n\t//   - error: ErrFileNotFound, ErrIsDirectory, etc.\n\tDownload(ctx context.Context, req DownloadRequest) (*DownloadResult, error)\n\n\t// StreamDownload returns a ReadCloser for streaming file download.\n\t//\n\t// Parameters:\n\t//   - ctx: Context for the streaming operation\n\t//   - req: Download request\n\t//\n\t// Returns:\n\t//   - io.ReadCloser: Stream for reading file data\n\t//   - error: ErrFileNotFound, ErrSandboxUnavailable, etc.\n\tStreamDownload(ctx context.Context, req DownloadRequest) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n\n\t// List lists directory contents with optional filtering and pagination.\n\t//\n\t// Parameters:\n\t//   - ctx: Context for the operation\n\t//   - req: List request containing path and options\n\t//\n\t// Returns:\n\t//   - *ListResult: Result containing file entries and pagination info\n\t//   - error: ErrFileNotFound, ErrNotDirectory, etc.\n\tList(ctx context.Context, req ListRequest) (*ListResult, error)\n\n\t// Delete deletes a file or directory.\n\t//\n\t// Parameters:\n\t//   - ctx: Context for the operation\n\t//   - req: Delete request containing path and options\n\t//\n\t// Returns:\n\t//   - error: nil on success, ErrFileNotFound, ErrDirectoryNotEmpty, etc.\n\tDelete(ctx context.Context, req DeleteRequest) error\n\n\t// Move moves/renames a file or directory.\n\t//\n\t// Parameters:\n\t//   - ctx: Context for the operation\n\t//   - req: Move request containing source and destination\n\t//\n\t// Returns:\n\t//   - error: nil on success, ErrFileNotFound, ErrFileExists, etc.\n\tMove(ctx context.Context, req MoveRequest) error\n\n\t// Copy copies a file or directory.\n\t//\n\t// Parameters:\n\t//   - ctx: Context for the operation\n\t//   - req: Copy request containing source and destination\n\t//\n\t// Returns:\n\t//   - error: nil on success, ErrFileNotFound, ErrQuotaExceeded, etc.\n\tCopy(ctx context.Context, req CopyRequest) error\n\n\t// Mkdir creates a directory.\n\t//\n\t// Parameters:\n\t//   - ctx: Context for the operation\n\t//   - req: Mkdir request containing path and permissions\n\t//\n\t// Returns:\n\t//   - error: nil on success, ErrFileExists, ErrPathTraversal, etc.\n\tMkdir(ctx context.Context, req MkdirRequest) error\n\n\t// Rmdir removes a directory (must be empty unless recursive).\n\t//\n\t// Parameters:\n\t//   - ctx: Context for the operation\n\t//   - req: Rmdir request containing path\n\t//\n\t// Returns:\n\t//   - error: nil on success, ErrDirectoryNotEmpty, etc.\n\tRmdir(ctx context.Context, req RmdirRequest) error\n\n\t// GetMetadata retrieves file metadata.\n\t//\n\t// Parameters:\n\t//   - ctx: Context for the operation\n\t//   - req: Metadata request containing path\n\t//\n\t// Returns:\n\t//   - *FileMetadata: Metadata including permissions and info\n\t//   - error: ErrFileNotFound, etc.\n\tGetMetadata(ctx context.Context, req MetadataRequest) (*FileMetadata, error)\n\n\t// SetPermissions sets file permissions.\n\t//\n\t// Parameters:\n\t//   - ctx: Context for the operation\n\t//   - sessionID: Target session ID\n\t//   - path: File path\n\t//   - mode: New permissions\n\t//\n\t// Returns:\n\t//   - error: nil on success, ErrFileNotFound, ErrPermissionDenied, etc.\n\tSetPermissions(ctx context.Context, sessionID, path string, mode os.FileMode) error\n\n\t// GetQuota retrieves quota information for a session.\n\t//\n\t// Parameters:\n\t//   - ctx: Context for the operation\n\t//   - sessionID: Target session ID\n\t//\n\t// Returns:\n\t//   - *QuotaInfo: Quota usage and limits\n\t//   - error: ErrSandboxUnavailable, etc.\n\tGetQuota(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*QuotaInfo, error)\n\n\t// Watch starts watching a path for file system changes.\n\t//\n\t// Parameters:\n\t//   - ctx: Context for the watch lifecycle\n\t//   - req: Watch request containing path and event filters\n\t//\n\t// Returns:\n\t//   - FileWatcher: Watcher for receiving events\n\t//   - error: ErrFileNotFound, etc.\n\tWatch(ctx context.Context, req WatchRequest) (FileWatcher, error)\n}\n```\n\n### Service Interfaces\n\n```go\n// SandboxResolver resolves session IDs to sandbox information.\ntype SandboxResolver interface {\n\t// Resolve returns sandbox info for a session ID.\n\t// Returns ErrSandboxNotFound if session doesn't exist.\n\tResolve(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n\n// SandboxFileOps performs file operations in a sandbox.\ntype SandboxFileOps interface {\n\t// ReadFile reads a file from the sandbox\n\tReadFile(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, path string) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n\n\t// WriteFile writes a file to the sandbox\n\tWriteFile(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, path string, reader io.Reader, size int64) error\n\n\t// DeleteFile deletes a file or directory\n\tDeleteFile(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, path string, recursive bool) error\n\n\t// MoveFile moves/renames a file\n\tMoveFile(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, src, dst string) error\n\n\t// CopyFile copies a file\n\tCopyFile(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, src, dst string) error\n\n\t// ListDirectory lists directory contents\n\tListDirectory(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, path string, recursive bool) ([]FileInfo, error)\n\n\t// CreateDirectory creates a directory\n\tCreateDirectory(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, path string, mode os.FileMode, parents bool) error\n\n\t// RemoveDirectory removes a directory\n\tRemoveDirectory(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, path string) error\n\n\t// GetFileInfo retrieves file information\n\tGetFileInfo(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, path string) (*FileInfo, error)\n\n\t// SetPermissions sets file permissions\n\tSetPermissions(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, path string, mode os.FileMode) error\n\n\t// GetDiskUsage retrieves disk usage for the sandbox\n\tGetDiskUsage(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) (*QuotaInfo, error)\n}\n\n// PicoDService provides high-level PicoD operations.\ntype PicoDService interface {\n\t// FileManager returns the file manager.\n\tFileManager() FileManager\n\n\t// CommandExecutor returns the command executor (from AR-015).\n\tCommandExecutor() CommandExecutor\n\n\t// Health returns the service health status.\n\tHealth(ctx context.Context) error\n\n\t// Shutdown gracefully shuts down the service.\n\tShutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Categories and Codes\n\n| Error | Code | Description | Retryable | Handling Strategy |\n|-------|------|-------------|-----------|-------------------|\n| `ErrInvalidRequest` | `INVALID_REQUEST` | Malformed file operation request | No | Return with field details |\n| `ErrInvalidSessionID` | `INVALID_SESSION_ID` | Missing or invalid session ID | No | Return 400 |\n| `ErrInvalidPath` | `INVALID_PATH` | Empty or invalid path | No | Return 400 |\n| `ErrPathTraversal` | `PATH_TRAVERSAL` | Detected path traversal attempt | No | Return 403, log security event |\n| `ErrPathNotAllowed` | `PATH_NOT_ALLOWED` | Path outside workspace | No | Return 403 |\n| `ErrFileNotFound` | `FILE_NOT_FOUND` | Specified path does not exist | No | Return 404 |\n| `ErrFileExists` | `FILE_EXISTS` | File already exists (no overwrite) | No | Return 409 |\n| `ErrIsDirectory` | `IS_DIRECTORY` | Expected file but got directory | No | Return 400 |\n| `ErrNotDirectory` | `NOT_DIRECTORY` | Expected directory but got file | No | Return 400 |\n| `ErrDirectoryNotEmpty` | `DIRECTORY_NOT_EMPTY` | Cannot delete non-empty dir | No | Return 400 |\n| `ErrQuotaExceeded` | `QUOTA_EXCEEDED` | Storage quota limit reached | No | Return 413 |\n| `ErrPermissionDenied` | `PERMISSION_DENIED` | Insufficient permissions | No | Return 403 |\n| `ErrTransferFailed` | `TRANSFER_FAILED` | Upload/download operation failed | Yes | Retry with backoff |\n| `ErrChecksumMismatch` | `CHECKSUM_MISMATCH` | Data integrity check failed | Yes | Retry upload |\n| `ErrSandboxUnavailable` | `SANDBOX_UNAVAILABLE` | Sandbox not accessible | Yes | Retry with backoff |\n| `ErrUploadSessionNotFound` | `UPLOAD_SESSION_NOT_FOUND` | Invalid upload session | No | Return 404 |\n| `ErrUploadSessionExpired` | `UPLOAD_SESSION_EXPIRED` | Upload session timeout | No | Return 410 |\n\n### Sentinel Errors\n\n```go\n// PicoD file operation errors\nvar (\n\tErrInvalidRequest              = errors.New(\"picod: invalid request\")\n\tErrInvalidSessionID            = errors.New(\"picod: session ID is required\")\n\tErrInvalidSourcePath           = errors.New(\"picod: source path is required\")\n\tErrInvalidDestinationPath      = errors.New(\"picod: destination path is required\")\n\tErrInvalidPath                 = errors.New(\"picod: path is required\")\n\tErrPathTraversal               = errors.New(\"picod: path traversal detected\")\n\tErrPathNotAllowed              = errors.New(\"picod: path outside workspace\")\n\tErrFileNotFound                = errors.New(\"picod: file not found\")\n\tErrFileExists                  = errors.New(\"picod: file already exists\")\n\tErrIsDirectory                 = errors.New(\"picod: path is a directory\")\n\tErrNotDirectory                = errors.New(\"picod: path is not a directory\")\n\tErrDirectoryNotEmpty           = errors.New(\"picod: directory not empty\")\n\tErrQuotaExceeded               = errors.New(\"picod: storage quota exceeded\")\n\tErrPermissionDenied            = errors.New(\"picod: permission denied\")\n\tErrTransferFailed              = errors.New(\"picod: file transfer failed\")\n\tErrChecksumMismatch            = errors.New(\"picod: checksum verification failed\")\n\tErrSandboxUnavailable          = errors.New(\"picod: sandbox unavailable\")\n\tErrUploadSessionNotFound       = errors.New(\"picod: upload session not found\")\n\tErrUploadSessionExpired        = errors.New(\"picod: upload session expired\")\n)\n```\n\n### FileError Structure\n\n```go\n// FileError represents a file operation error with context.\ntype FileError struct {\n\t// Code is the machine-readable error code\n\tCode string `json:\"code\"`\n\n\t// Message is the human-readable error message\n\tMessage string `json:\"message\"`\n\n\t// Path is the file path related to the error\n\tPath string `json:\"path,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// Details contains additional error context\n\tDetails map[string]interface{} `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// Error returns the error string.\nfunc (e *FileError) Error() string {\n\tif e.Path != \"\" {\n\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s (path=%s)\", e.Code, e.Message, e.Path)\n\t}\n\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s\", e.Code, e.Message)\n}\n\n// NewFileError creates a new FileError.\nfunc NewFileError(code, message, path string) *FileError {\n\treturn &FileError{\n\t\tCode:    code,\n\t\tMessage: message,\n\t\tPath:    path,\n\t}\n}\n\n// WithDetails adds details to the error.\nfunc (e *FileError) WithDetails(details map[string]interface{}) *FileError {\n\te.Details = details\n\treturn e\n}\n```\n\n### Error Handling Patterns\n\n#### Upload Error Handling\n\n```go\nfunc (fm *fileManager) Upload(ctx context.Context, req UploadRequest) (*UploadResult, error) {\n\t// Validate request\n\tif err := req.Validate(); err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrInvalidRequest, err)\n\t}\n\n\t// Validate path\n\tpathResult, err := fm.validator.Validate(req.DestinationPath)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\n\t// Check if file exists (and overwrite not allowed)\n\tif !req.Overwrite {\n\t\texists, err := fm.fileExists(ctx, req.SessionID, pathResult.AbsolutePath)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: failed to check file existence: %v\", ErrSandboxUnavailable, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\tif exists {\n\t\t\treturn nil, NewFileError(ErrorCodeFileExists, \"file already exists\", req.DestinationPath)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Check quota if size is known\n\tif req.TotalSize > 0 {\n\t\tif err := fm.quotaManager.CheckUpload(ctx, req.SessionID, req.TotalSize); err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, err\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Resolve sandbox\n\tsandbox, err := fm.sandboxResolver.Resolve(ctx, req.SessionID)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrSandboxUnavailable, err)\n\t}\n\n\t// Perform upload with timeout\n\tuploadCtx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, fm.config.UploadSessionTimeout)\n\tdefer cancel()\n\n\tresult, err := fm.performUpload(uploadCtx, sandbox, req, pathResult)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tif errors.Is(err, context.DeadlineExceeded) {\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: upload timeout exceeded\", ErrTransferFailed)\n\t\t}\n\t\tif errors.Is(err, context.Canceled) {\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: upload was cancelled\", ErrTransferFailed)\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrTransferFailed, err)\n\t}\n\n\t// Update quota\n\tif err := fm.quotaManager.UpdateQuota(ctx, req.SessionID, result.Size, 1); err != nil {\n\t\t// Log but don't fail - quota will be consistent on next check\n\t\tlog.Printf(\"warning: failed to update quota: %v\", err)\n\t}\n\n\treturn result, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### Path Validation Error Handling\n\n```go\nfunc (fm *fileManager) validatePath(ctx context.Context, sessionID, path string, mustExist bool) (*ValidationResult, error) {\n\t// Validate path format\n\tresult, err := fm.validator.Validate(path)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tif errors.Is(err, ErrPathTraversal) {\n\t\t\t// Log security event\n\t\t\tfm.logSecurityEvent(ctx, sessionID, \"path_traversal_attempt\", map[string]string{\n\t\t\t\t\"path\": path,\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t\treturn nil, NewFileError(ErrorCodePathTraversal, \"path traversal detected\", path)\n\t\t}\n\t\tif errors.Is(err, ErrPathNotAllowed) {\n\t\t\treturn nil, NewFileError(ErrorCodePathNotAllowed, \"path outside workspace\", path)\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\n\t// Check existence if required\n\tif mustExist {\n\t\texists, err := fm.fileExists(ctx, sessionID, result.AbsolutePath)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: failed to check file: %v\", ErrSandboxUnavailable, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\tif !exists {\n\t\t\treturn nil, NewFileError(ErrorCodeFileNotFound, \"file not found\", path)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn result, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### Quota Enforcement\n\n```go\nfunc (qm *quotaManager) CheckUpload(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, size int64) error {\n\tquota, err := qm.GetQuota(ctx, sessionID)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"%w: failed to get quota: %v\", ErrSandboxUnavailable, err)\n\t}\n\n\t// Check total bytes limit\n\tif quota.TotalBytes > 0 && size > quota.AvailableBytes {\n\t\treturn NewFileError(ErrorCodeQuotaExceeded,\n\t\t\tfmt.Sprintf(\"upload size %d exceeds available quota %d\", size, quota.AvailableBytes),\n\t\t\t\"\").\n\t\t\tWithDetails(map[string]interface{}{\n\t\t\t\t\"requested\": size,\n\t\t\t\t\"available\": quota.AvailableBytes,\n\t\t\t\t\"total\":     quota.TotalBytes,\n\t\t\t})\n\t}\n\n\t// Check file count limit\n\tif quota.MaxFileCount > 0 && quota.FileCount >= quota.MaxFileCount {\n\t\treturn NewFileError(ErrorCodeQuotaExceeded,\n\t\t\tfmt.Sprintf(\"file count limit %d reached\", quota.MaxFileCount),\n\t\t\t\"\").\n\t\t\tWithDetails(map[string]interface{}{\n\t\t\t\t\"current\": quota.FileCount,\n\t\t\t\t\"limit\":   quota.MaxFileCount,\n\t\t\t})\n\t}\n\n\treturn nil\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestFileManager_Upload_Success(t *testing.T) {\n\t// Setup mocks\n\tmockQuota := new(mockQuotaManager)\n\tmockResolver := new(mockSandboxResolver)\n\tmockSandboxOps := new(mockSandboxFileOps)\n\n\tfm := NewFileManager(FileManagerConfig{}, mockQuota, mockResolver, mockSandboxOps)\n\n\t// Setup expectations\n\tsandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{\n\t\tSessionID: \"sess-123\",\n\t\tPodIP:     \"10.0.0.1\",\n\t}\n\tmockResolver.On(\"Resolve\", mock.Anything, \"sess-123\").Return(sandbox, nil)\n\tmockQuota.On(\"CheckUpload\", mock.Anything, \"sess-123\", int64(1024)).Return(nil)\n\tmockSandboxOps.On(\"WriteFile\", mock.Anything, sandbox, \"/workspace/test.txt\", mock.Anything, int64(1024)).Return(nil)\n\tmockQuota.On(\"UpdateQuota\", mock.Anything, \"sess-123\", int64(1024), int64(1)).Return(nil)\n\n\t// Execute\n\tresult, err := fm.Upload(context.Background(), UploadRequest{\n\t\tSessionID:       \"sess-123\",\n\t\tSourcePath:      \"/tmp/test.txt\",\n\t\tDestinationPath: \"test.txt\",\n\t\tTotalSize:       1024,\n\t})\n\n\t// Assert\n\tassert.NoError(t, err)\n\tassert.NotEmpty(t, result.FileID)\n\tassert.Equal(t, \"test.txt\", result.Path)\n\tassert.Equal(t, int64(1024), result.Size)\n\tmockResolver.AssertExpectations(t)\n\tmockQuota.AssertExpectations(t)\n\tmockSandboxOps.AssertExpectations(t)\n}\n\nfunc TestFileManager_Upload_PathTraversal(t *testing.T) {\n\tfm := NewFileManager(DefaultFileManagerConfig(), nil, nil, nil)\n\tfm.validator = &PathValidator{WorkspaceRoot: \"/workspace\"}\n\n\t_, err := fm.Upload(context.Background(), UploadRequest{\n\t\tSessionID:       \"sess-123\",\n\t\tSourcePath:      \"/tmp/test.txt\",\n\t\tDestinationPath: \"../../../etc/passwd\",\n\t})\n\n\tassert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrPathTraversal)\n\tfileErr, ok := err.(*FileError)\n\tassert.True(t, ok)\n\tassert.Equal(t, ErrorCodePathTraversal, fileErr.Code)\n}\n\nfunc TestFileManager_Upload_QuotaExceeded(t *testing.T) {\n\tmockQuota := new(mockQuotaManager)\n\tfm := NewFileManager(DefaultFileManagerConfig(), mockQuota, nil, nil)\n\tfm.validator = &PathValidator{WorkspaceRoot: \"/workspace\"}\n\n\tmockQuota.On(\"CheckUpload\", mock.Anything, \"sess-123\", int64(1024*1024*1024)).Return(\n\t\tNewFileError(ErrorCodeQuotaExceeded, \"quota exceeded\", \"\"),\n\t)\n\n\t_, err := fm.Upload(context.Background(), UploadRequest{\n\t\tSessionID:       \"sess-123\",\n\t\tSourcePath:      \"/tmp/large.bin\",\n\t\tDestinationPath: \"large.bin\",\n\t\tTotalSize:       1024 * 1024 * 1024,\n\t})\n\n\tassert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrQuotaExceeded)\n}\n\nfunc TestFileManager_Download_NotFound(t *testing.T) {\n\tmockResolver := new(mockSandboxResolver)\n\tmockSandboxOps := new(mockSandboxFileOps)\n\n\tfm := NewFileManager(DefaultFileManagerConfig(), nil, mockResolver, mockSandboxOps)\n\tfm.validator = &PathValidator{WorkspaceRoot: \"/workspace\"}\n\n\tsandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{SessionID: \"sess-123\"}\n\tmockResolver.On(\"Resolve\", mock.Anything, \"sess-123\").Return(sandbox, nil)\n\tmockSandboxOps.On(\"GetFileInfo\", mock.Anything, sandbox, \"/workspace/missing.txt\").Return(nil, ErrFileNotFound)\n\n\t_, err := fm.Download(context.Background(), DownloadRequest{\n\t\tSessionID: \"sess-123\",\n\t\tPath:      \"missing.txt\",\n\t})\n\n\tassert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrFileNotFound)\n}\n\nfunc TestFileManager_List_Success(t *testing.T) {\n\tmockResolver := new(mockSandboxResolver)\n\tmockSandboxOps := new(mockSandboxFileOps)\n\n\tfm := NewFileManager(DefaultFileManagerConfig(), nil, mockResolver, mockSandboxOps)\n\tfm.validator = &PathValidator{WorkspaceRoot: \"/workspace\"}\n\n\tsandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{SessionID: \"sess-123\"}\n\tmockResolver.On(\"Resolve\", mock.Anything, \"sess-123\").Return(sandbox, nil)\n\n\tentries := []FileInfo{\n\t\t{Name: \"file1.txt\", Path: \"file1.txt\", Type: FileTypeFile, Size: 100},\n\t\t{Name: \"file2.go\", Path: \"file2.go\", Type: FileTypeFile, Size: 200},\n\t\t{Name: \"subdir\", Path: \"subdir\", Type: FileTypeDirectory},\n\t}\n\tmockSandboxOps.On(\"ListDirectory\", mock.Anything, sandbox, \"/workspace\", false).Return(entries, nil)\n\n\tresult, err := fm.List(context.Background(), ListRequest{\n\t\tSessionID: \"sess-123\",\n\t\tPath:      \".\",\n\t})\n\n\tassert.NoError(t, err)\n\tassert.Len(t, result.Entries, 3)\n\tassert.Equal(t, 3, result.TotalCount)\n}\n\nfunc TestFileManager_List_WithPatternFilter(t *testing.T) {\n\tmockResolver := new(mockSandboxResolver)\n\tmockSandboxOps := new(mockSandboxFileOps)\n\n\tfm := NewFileManager(DefaultFileManagerConfig(), nil, mockResolver, mockSandboxOps)\n\tfm.validator = &PathValidator{WorkspaceRoot: \"/workspace\"}\n\n\tsandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{SessionID: \"sess-123\"}\n\tmockResolver.On(\"Resolve\", mock.Anything, \"sess-123\").Return(sandbox, nil)\n\n\tentries := []FileInfo{\n\t\t{Name: \"file1.txt\", Path: \"file1.txt\", Type: FileTypeFile},\n\t\t{Name: \"file2.go\", Path: \"file2.go\", Type: FileTypeFile},\n\t\t{Name: \"file3.txt\", Path: \"file3.txt\", Type: FileTypeFile},\n\t}\n\tmockSandboxOps.On(\"ListDirectory\", mock.Anything, sandbox, \"/workspace\", false).Return(entries, nil)\n\n\tresult, err := fm.List(context.Background(), ListRequest{\n\t\tSessionID: \"sess-123\",\n\t\tPath:      \".\",\n\t\tPattern:   \"*.txt\",\n\t})\n\n\tassert.NoError(t, err)\n\t// Note: Pattern filtering is done by the implementation after fetching\n\t// This test verifies the List call succeeds\n}\n\nfunc TestPathValidator_Validate_Success(t *testing.T) {\n\tvalidator := &PathValidator{WorkspaceRoot: \"/workspace\"}\n\n\tresult, err := validator.Validate(\"subdir/file.txt\")\n\n\tassert.NoError(t, err)\n\tassert.Equal(t, \"subdir/file.txt\", result.CleanedPath)\n\tassert.Equal(t, \"/workspace/subdir/file.txt\", result.AbsolutePath)\n\tassert.True(t, result.IsWithinWorkspace)\n}\n\nfunc TestPathValidator_Validate_PathTraversal(t *testing.T) {\n\tvalidator := &PathValidator{WorkspaceRoot: \"/workspace\"}\n\n\t_, err := validator.Validate(\"../etc/passwd\")\n\tassert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrPathTraversal)\n\n\t_, err = validator.Validate(\"subdir/../../../etc/passwd\")\n\tassert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrPathTraversal)\n}\n\nfunc TestPathValidator_Validate_AbsolutePath(t *testing.T) {\n\tvalidator := &PathValidator{WorkspaceRoot: \"/workspace\"}\n\n\t_, err := validator.Validate(\"/etc/passwd\")\n\tassert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrPathNotAllowed)\n}\n\nfunc TestQuotaManager_CheckUpload_Success(t *testing.T) {\n\tqm := &quotaManager{}\n\tqm.store = new(mockQuotaStore)\n\n\tquota := &QuotaInfo{\n\t\tSessionID:      \"sess-123\",\n\t\tUsedBytes:      100,\n\t\tTotalBytes:     1000,\n\t\tAvailableBytes: 900,\n\t\tFileCount:      5,\n\t\tMaxFileCount:   100,\n\t}\n\tqm.store.(*mockQuotaStore).On(\"GetQuota\", mock.Anything, \"sess-123\").Return(quota, nil)\n\n\terr := qm.CheckUpload(context.Background(), \"sess-123\", 500)\n\tassert.NoError(t, err)\n}\n\nfunc TestQuotaManager_CheckUpload_Exceeded(t *testing.T) {\n\tqm := &quotaManager{}\n\tqm.store = new(mockQuotaStore)\n\n\tquota := &QuotaInfo{\n\t\tSessionID:      \"sess-123\",\n\t\tUsedBytes:      900,\n\t\tTotalBytes:     1000,\n\t\tAvailableBytes: 100,\n\t\tFileCount:      5,\n\t\tMaxFileCount:   100,\n\t}\n\tqm.store.(*mockQuotaStore).On(\"GetQuota\", mock.Anything, \"sess-123\").Return(quota, nil)\n\n\terr := qm.CheckUpload(context.Background(), \"sess-123\", 500)\n\tassert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrQuotaExceeded)\n}\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestIntegration_FileOperations(t *testing.T) {\n\tif testing.Short() {\n\t\tt.Skip(\"Skipping integration test\")\n\t}\n\n\t// Setup real store and sandbox\n\tstore := setupTestStore(t)\n\tdefer store.Close()\n\n\tsandbox := setupTestSandbox(t)\n\tdefer sandbox.Cleanup()\n\n\tfm := NewFileManager(DefaultFileManagerConfig(), store, sandbox.Resolver, sandbox.FileOps)\n\n\t// Test upload\n\tuploadResult, err := fm.Upload(context.Background(), UploadRequest{\n\t\tSessionID:       sandbox.SessionID,\n\t\tSourcePath:      \"/tmp/test.txt\",\n\t\tDestinationPath: \"test.txt\",\n\t})\n\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\tassert.NotEmpty(t, uploadResult.FileID)\n\n\t// Test list\n\tlistResult, err := fm.List(context.Background(), ListRequest{\n\t\tSessionID: sandbox.SessionID,\n\t\tPath:      \".\",\n\t})\n\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\tassert.Len(t, listResult.Entries, 1)\n\n\t// Test download\n\tdownloadResult, err := fm.Download(context.Background(), DownloadRequest{\n\t\tSessionID: sandbox.SessionID,\n\t\tPath:      \"test.txt\",\n\t})\n\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\tdefer downloadResult.Data.Close()\n\n\t// Test delete\n\terr = fm.Delete(context.Background(), DeleteRequest{\n\t\tSessionID: sandbox.SessionID,\n\t\tPath:      \"test.txt\",\n\t})\n\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\n\t// Verify deletion\n\t_, err = fm.GetMetadata(context.Background(), MetadataRequest{\n\t\tSessionID: sandbox.SessionID,\n\t\tPath:      \"test.txt\",\n\t})\n\tassert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrFileNotFound)\n}\n\nfunc TestIntegration_ChunkedUpload(t *testing.T) {\n\tif testing.Short() {\n\t\tt.Skip(\"Skipping integration test\")\n\t}\n\n\tsandbox := setupTestSandbox(t)\n\tdefer sandbox.Cleanup()\n\n\tfm := NewFileManager(DefaultFileManagerConfig(), nil, sandbox.Resolver, sandbox.FileOps)\n\n\t// Initialize chunked upload\n\tuploadID := \"test-upload-123\"\n\tsession := &uploadSession{\n\t\tID:          uploadID,\n\t\tSessionID:   sandbox.SessionID,\n\t\tDestination: \"large.bin\",\n\t\tTotalSize:   1024,\n\t\tChunkSize:   512,\n\t\tChunks:      make(map[int]bool),\n\t\tTempDir:     t.TempDir(),\n\t\tCreatedAt:   time.Now(),\n\t}\n\tfm.uploadSessions[uploadID] = session\n\n\t// Upload chunks\n\tfor i := 0; i < 2; i++ {\n\t\tchunkData := make([]byte, 512)\n\t\trand.Read(chunkData)\n\n\t\tresult, err := fm.UploadChunk(context.Background(), UploadChunkRequest{\n\t\t\tUploadID:   uploadID,\n\t\t\tChunkIndex: i,\n\t\t\tChunkData:  bytes.NewReader(chunkData),\n\t\t\tChunkSize:  512,\n\t\t\tIsLast:     i == 1,\n\t\t})\n\t\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n\t\tassert.Equal(t, i, result.ChunkIndex)\n\t\tassert.Equal(t, i == 1, result.UploadComplete)\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n### Test Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Test Case | Expected Result |\n|----------|-----------|-----------------|\n| Upload small file | `TestUpload_Success` | Returns UploadResult with correct checksum |\n| Upload large file (chunked) | `TestChunkedUpload_Success` | All chunks received, assembled correctly |\n| Upload to existing path (no overwrite) | `TestUpload_FileExists` | Returns ErrFileExists |\n| Path traversal attempt | `TestUpload_PathTraversal` | Returns ErrPathTraversal, logs security event |\n| Absolute path upload | `TestUpload_AbsolutePath` | Returns ErrPathNotAllowed |\n| Quota exceeded | `TestUpload_QuotaExceeded` | Returns ErrQuotaExceeded |\n| Download file | `TestDownload_Success` | Returns correct data with matching checksum |\n| Download missing file | `TestDownload_NotFound` | Returns ErrFileNotFound |\n| Download directory (no recursive) | `TestDownload_IsDirectory` | Returns ErrIsDirectory |\n| List directory | `TestList_Success` | Returns all entries with correct metadata |\n| List with pattern filter | `TestList_WithPattern` | Returns only matching entries |\n| Delete file | `TestDelete_Success` | File removed, quota updated |\n| Delete non-empty directory | `TestDelete_DirectoryNotEmpty` | Returns ErrDirectoryNotEmpty |\n| Move file | `TestMove_Success` | File moved to new location |\n| Copy file | `TestCopy_Success` | File copied to new location |\n| Mkdir | `TestMkdir_Success` | Directory created |\n| Rmdir | `TestRmdir_Success` | Directory removed |\n| GetMetadata | `TestGetMetadata_Success` | Returns complete metadata |\n| Watch directory | `TestWatch_Success` | Receives file events |\n| Concurrent uploads | `TestConcurrentUploads` | All succeed or appropriate errors |\n| Upload timeout | `TestUpload_Timeout` | Returns ErrTransferFailed |\n| Checksum mismatch | `TestUpload_ChecksumMismatch` | Returns ErrChecksumMismatch |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### External Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/google/uuid` | v1.6.0 | FileID/UploadID generation |\n| `github.com/klauspost/compress` | Latest | Archive compression (zip/tar.gz) |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes API client |\n\n### Internal Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo shared types |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Quota store interface |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod` | Shared PicoD types (AR-015) |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| Session Manager | File operations within user sessions |\n| CLI Tooling | `kubectl-agentcube cp` commands |\n| HTTP API Layer | REST endpoints for file management |\n| IDE Integration | File sync for remote development |\n\n---\n\n## Performance Characteristics\n\n| Operation | Complexity | Latency | Notes |\n|-----------|------------|---------|-------|\n| Upload (small) | O(n) | n = file size | Direct upload with streaming |\n| Upload (chunked) | O(n) | n = total size | Chunk assembly overhead minimal |\n| Download | O(n) | n = file size | Streaming with buffering |\n| List (non-recursive) | O(m) | m = entries | Single directory listing |\n| List (recursive) | O(m) | m = total entries | Tree walk |\n| Delete | O(1) | Per file/directory | Recursive delete O(n) for n files |\n| Move/Copy | O(1) | Metadata op | Copy involves data transfer O(n) |\n| Quota Check | O(1) | Cached value | Periodic sync with store |\n| Watch | O(1) | Event-driven | Background goroutine per watch |\n\n### Resource Limits\n\n| Resource | Default | Maximum | Configurable |\n|----------|---------|---------|--------------|\n| Max upload size | 1GB | 10GB | Yes |\n| Chunk size | 16MB | 64MB | Yes |\n| Concurrent uploads | 5 | 20 | Yes |\n| Concurrent downloads | 5 | 20 | Yes |\n| Stream buffer | 32KB | 1MB | Yes |\n| Upload session timeout | 1h | 24h | Yes |\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n- **Path Traversal Prevention**: Rejects `..` patterns and validates all paths within workspace\n- **Workspace Isolation**: All operations confined to sandbox-specific workspace root\n- **Symlink Resolution**: Resolves and validates symlinks before operations\n- **Quota Enforcement**: Prevents storage exhaustion via size and file count limits\n- **Permission Validation**: Checks read/write/execute permissions before operations\n- **Content Validation**: Optional MIME type validation for uploads\n- **Audit Logging**: Logs all file operations with session ID and path info\n- **Sandbox Boundary Enforcement**: Validates resolved paths remain within workspace\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [PicoD Proposal](proposal.md) — Feature proposal and requirements\n- [PicoD Delta Spec](changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md) — API specification changes\n- [PicoD Tests](changes/AR-016/tests.md) — Test specifications\n- [AR-015 Command Execution](changes/AR-015/design.md) — Related command execution API\n- [AR-009 Sandbox](sandbox-orchestration/design.md) — Sandbox orchestration system\n- [AR-012 Session Store](session-store/design.md) — Storage interface\n- [client-go Library](deployment/client-go.md) — Kubernetes client patterns\n\n---\n\n*AR-016 — Module: pkg/picod — Language: Go — Size: M*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/go.mod":[{"range":{"start":{"line":18,"character":42},"end":{"line":18,"character":53}},"severity":2,"source":"go mod tidy","message":"github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2 should be direct"},{"range":{"start":{"line":35,"character":31},"end":{"line":35,"character":42}},"severity":2,"source":"go mod tidy","message":"github.com/google/uuid should be direct"}]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775875693213,"end":1775875694142}}}}
